{"term":"1957","caseName":"Moog Industries, Inc. v. Federal Trade Commission","caseLink":"https://www.oyez.org/cases/1957/77","caseTranscripts":[{"transcriptTitle":"Oral Argument, Part 1: Moog Industries, Inc. v. FTC - January 14, 1958 (77)","transcriptLink":"https://apps.oyez.org/player/#/warren6/oral_argument_audio/13517","transcript":[{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Number 77, Moog Industries, Incorporated, Petitioner, versus Federal Trade Commission.","start":0,"stop":34.763,"duration":34.76},{"text":"Mr. Frank.","start":34.763,"stop":36.867,"duration":2.1}]},{"speakerName":"Malcolm I. Frank","textObjs":[{"text":"May it please the Court.","start":36.867,"stop":40.967,"duration":4.1},{"text":"This is the case on review from the Eighth Circuit to review the refusal of an order in a motion requested by the petitioner for the Court to exercise its equitable jurisdiction to stay in order to cease and desist issued by the Federal Trade Commission.","start":40.967,"stop":74.985,"duration":34.02},{"text":"That's the sole issue in this case.","start":74.985,"stop":82.618,"duration":7.63},{"text":"In 1949, the Federal Trade Commission filed a complaint against the petitioner alleging that it had discriminated in prices along it's purchasers in violation of Section 2 (a) of the Robinson-Patman Act.","start":82.618,"stop":109.964,"duration":27.35},{"text":"That discrimination consisted of offering volume discounts to all of its customers.","start":109.964,"stop":121.496,"duration":11.53},{"text":"That discount being in the form of an annual discount based on the volume of purchases, 2000 to 3000, 3000 to 4000, 4000 to 6000 and so on.","start":121.496,"stop":139.883,"duration":18.39},{"text":"It's set out in the record, each amount being a larger discount.","start":139.883,"stop":145.26,"duration":5.38},{"text":"The record shows that that discount in some form or other, that volume discount is more or less standard practice in the Automotive Replacement Parts Industry.","start":145.26,"stop":163.09,"duration":17.83},{"text":"The Automotive Replacement Parts Industry consists of many different things.","start":163.09,"stop":168.507,"duration":5.42},{"text":"In the case of Moog Industries for the sake of convenience, they have leaf springs, chassis part, coil actions and piston rings.","start":168.507,"stop":180.406,"duration":11.9},{"text":"They have three classifications.","start":180.406,"stop":184.416,"duration":4.01},{"text":"Several thousand parts intervene the lowest various classifications adoptable to cars going back as far as 1937, the various types of car.","start":184.416,"stop":200.907,"duration":16.49},{"text":"There's no question that these volume discounts were offered to all their customers.","start":200.907,"stop":207.895,"duration":6.99},{"text":"There is no question that it is standard practice in the industry to offer those discounts.","start":207.895,"stop":216.088,"duration":8.19},{"text":"The record shows that by testimony as we have referred to it in our brief in various places.","start":216.088,"stop":222.443,"duration":6.36},{"text":"In addition to that, there are exhibits attached to the record which show contracts for volume discounts, McQUay Norris, Regal Tool and Manufacturing, Thompson Products as typical contract showing those exhibits.","start":222.443,"stop":241.313,"duration":18.87}]},{"speakerName":"UNKNOWN","textObjs":[{"text":"Is this proof before the Commission?","start":241.313,"stop":243.632,"duration":2.32}]},{"speakerName":"Malcolm I. Frank","textObjs":[{"text":"All before the Commission.","start":243.632,"stop":245.209,"duration":1.58}]},{"speakerName":"William O. Douglas","textObjs":[{"text":"But we must assume there was a violation here.","start":245.209,"stop":249.421,"duration":4.21},{"text":"We don't have a question of the merits.","start":249.421,"stop":251.225,"duration":1.8}]},{"speakerName":"Malcolm I. Frank","textObjs":[{"text":"The merits of this case and not before the Court.","start":251.225,"stop":253.81,"duration":2.59}]},{"speakerName":"William O. Douglas","textObjs":[{"text":"So we assume there's a violation.","start":253.81,"stop":255.397,"duration":1.59}]},{"speakerName":"Malcolm I. Frank","textObjs":[{"text":"The Circuit Court of Appeals sue Justice Whittaker on the Eighth Circuit at that time, affirmed the decision of the Federal Trade Commission that there had been a violation.","start":255.397,"stop":271.228,"duration":15.83},{"text":"And in addition to that, notwithstanding the fact that the Commission has not sought an enforcement of the order, when they affirmed the decision, they ordered the petitioner to file its certificate of compliance within 60 days after the receipt of the order by the Federal Trade Commission.","start":271.228,"stop":296.458,"duration":25.23},{"text":"When that order was entered, we filed our motion to state that order and for the Court to exercise its equitable jurisdiction and hold it in the bench until our competitors in that industry were subjected to like orders.","start":296.458,"stop":315.654,"duration":19.2},{"text":"Otherwise, we would be placed at a severe competitive disadvantage.","start":315.654,"stop":322.014,"duration":6.36}]},{"speakerName":"William O. Douglas","textObjs":[{"text":"Were those competitors have been preceded against by the Commission at that time?","start":322.014,"stop":328.983,"duration":6.97}]},{"speakerName":"Malcolm I. Frank","textObjs":[{"text":"Out of the 18 or 20 that are named in the record, Justice Douglas.","start":328.983,"stop":338.961,"duration":9.98},{"text":"I think two of them were being preceded against at that time.","start":338.961,"stop":343.6,"duration":4.64},{"text":"In the nine years since this litigation has started, the Federal Trade Commission, according to its brief, has filed 14 to a proceedings against members of the Automotive Replacement Parts Industry.","start":343.6,"stop":362.65,"duration":19.05},{"text":"Out of those 14 complaints, only three of them are competitors of petitioner.","start":362.65,"stop":374.819,"duration":12.17}]},{"speakerName":"William O. Douglas","textObjs":[{"text":"Would it take another nine years to get it presented in this case?","start":374.819,"stop":378.679,"duration":3.86}]},{"speakerName":"Malcolm I. Frank","textObjs":[{"text":"It might take longer than that Justice Douglas.","start":378.679,"stop":381.547,"duration":2.87}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"18 (Inaudible)","start":381.547,"stop":383.903,"duration":2.36}]},{"speakerName":"Malcolm I. Frank","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, we named in the record there some 18 or 20 of them named.","start":383.903,"stop":390.807,"duration":6.9}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"That has taken nine years (Inaudible)","start":390.807,"stop":394.128,"duration":3.32}]},{"speakerName":"Malcolm I. Frank","textObjs":[{"text":"So far, there has been nine years of litigation as I construe this record from what the Federal Trade Commission brief says to proceed in nine cases.","start":394.128,"stop":414.346,"duration":20.22},{"text":"To date, they have filed nine cases but all together -- now, wait a minute, I'm wrong on that.","start":414.346,"stop":425.589,"duration":11.24},{"text":"They have filed 14 cases but all of them have not proceeded to a conclusion.","start":425.589,"stop":433.762,"duration":8.17},{"text":"For instance one against our largest competitor Thompson Products which had been going on for several years has not been brought to a decision to an initial decision by the hearing commissioner.","start":433.762,"stop":449.747,"duration":15.99},{"text":"There is no question in the record documentarily and from testimony that its standard practice in the industry.","start":449.747,"stop":461.231,"duration":11.48},{"text":"And the question arises what is the jurisdiction of the appellate court in a motion of that sort.","start":461.231,"stop":475.197,"duration":13.97},{"text":"It is my understanding, Your Honors that a motion of that sort is more or less ancillary to the proceeding for this reason.","start":475.197,"stop":487.872,"duration":12.68},{"text":"The Federal Trade Commission is not a judicial body, these (Inaudible) states.","start":487.872,"stop":495.485,"duration":7.61},{"text":"Therefore, it has no equitable jurisdiction.","start":495.485,"stop":499.535,"duration":4.05},{"text":"It can't decide questions of equity.","start":499.535,"stop":503.894,"duration":4.36},{"text":"So let us start first (Voice Overlap) to the jurisdiction of an appellate court by looking at what the statute says.","start":503.894,"stop":510.329,"duration":6.44}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"May I ask you whether that means, has no equity jurisdiction?Does that mean that the Commission would itself be powerless to enter or to qualify a order of finding illegality with such a qualification?","start":510.329,"stop":530.576,"duration":20.25}]},{"speakerName":"Malcolm I. Frank","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, Justice Frankfurter that is a good question and I'll say this in reply.","start":530.576,"stop":538.169,"duration":7.59},{"text":"A little bit further in my argument if I -- my time last that long.","start":538.169,"stop":544.005,"duration":5.84},{"text":"In the cosmetics industry, the Commission did do something just like that.","start":544.005,"stop":553.186,"duration":9.18},{"text":"They file eight or nine proceedings, one of them being against Elizabeth Arden.","start":553.186,"stop":562.405,"duration":9.22},{"text":"And while Elizabeth Arden was going on, they entered into agreement with the rest of the boys in the other cases to hold it up and not proceed with them and not make the -- the decree final against there -- Elizabeth Arden -- against the rest of them until Elizabeth Arden has been brought to a final conclusion.","start":562.405,"stop":586.54,"duration":24.13},{"text":"It is in their words, they used their discretion may I say that.","start":586.54,"stop":592.516,"duration":5.98},{"text":"I don't say that they have no discretion but they don't have due equitable jurisdiction.","start":592.516,"stop":600.056,"duration":7.54},{"text":"The Court has held that they are not a judicial body but they can use their discretion.","start":600.056,"stop":606.063,"duration":6.01},{"text":"I do know that they have filed --","start":606.063,"stop":609.107,"duration":3.04}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"If they hold up in the Elizabeth Arden case, that's not a bad target I suppose.","start":609.107,"stop":614.913,"duration":5.81},{"text":"If they hold up the enforcement of the order against Elizabeth Arden until they get through with the others?","start":614.913,"stop":619.947,"duration":5.03}]},{"speakerName":"Malcolm I. Frank","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, sir.","start":619.947,"stop":620.664,"duration":0.72},{"text":"They entered to a solemn agreement to do that.","start":620.664,"stop":623.147,"duration":2.48}]},{"speakerName":"William O. Douglas","textObjs":[{"text":"But those were the companion cases.","start":623.147,"stop":626.919,"duration":3.77}]},{"speakerName":"Malcolm I. Frank","textObjs":[{"text":"Sir?","start":626.919,"stop":627.598,"duration":0.68}]},{"speakerName":"William O. Douglas","textObjs":[{"text":"Those were companion cases.","start":627.598,"stop":629.231,"duration":1.63}]},{"speakerName":"Malcolm I. Frank","textObjs":[{"text":"No, there were against other concerns.","start":629.231,"stop":631.686,"duration":2.46}]},{"speakerName":"William O. Douglas","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, but I mean they were pending at the time.","start":631.686,"stop":634.101,"duration":2.41}]},{"speakerName":"Malcolm I. Frank","textObjs":[{"text":"I don't know whether they were all pending at the same time or not.","start":634.101,"stop":637.514,"duration":3.41}]},{"speakerName":"William O. Douglas","textObjs":[{"text":"But they were eight or nine and one was on appeal and they decided they hold (Inaudible).","start":637.514,"stop":641.834,"duration":4.32}]},{"speakerName":"Malcolm I. Frank","textObjs":[{"text":"They may have been all pending at the time.","start":641.834,"stop":645.257,"duration":3.42},{"text":"I don't know whether they were filed simultaneously or not Justice Douglas.","start":645.257,"stop":649.421,"duration":4.16},{"text":"But I do know that they entered into that agreement because of the -- so that one would not be competitively injured.","start":649.421,"stop":657.413,"duration":7.99},{"text":"They entered -- they would all be entered so that it would be effective at the same time.","start":657.413,"stop":664.301,"duration":6.89}]},{"speakerName":"William O. Douglas","textObjs":[{"text":"But this like -- here in this Court, we sometimes hold the case because other cases are about to require --","start":664.301,"stop":669.626,"duration":5.32}]},{"speakerName":"Malcolm I. Frank","textObjs":[{"text":"It's been done before.","start":669.626,"stop":670.941,"duration":1.32},{"text":"It was done in the Chrysler case.","start":670.941,"stop":672.927,"duration":1.99},{"text":"It was done in the Ford Motor case, the Justice Department has recognized.","start":672.927,"stop":677.069,"duration":4.14},{"text":"They entered into an agreement with Ford Motor Company and they entered in -- that they wouldn't hold that against them for -- any longer than it took to complete the General Motors case and if they weren't successful in the General Motors case the order in the Ford Motor case wouldn't be effective.","start":677.069,"stop":692.008,"duration":14.94}]},{"speakerName":"William O. Douglas","textObjs":[{"text":"I don't believe they would wait at nine years so.","start":692.008,"stop":694.8,"duration":2.79}]},{"speakerName":"Malcolm I. Frank","textObjs":[{"text":"Sir?","start":694.8,"stop":695.449,"duration":0.65}]},{"speakerName":"William O. Douglas","textObjs":[{"text":"I don't think that they would wait nine years.","start":695.449,"stop":699.511,"duration":4.06}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"There are two different questions at least to my mind.","start":699.511,"stop":702.064,"duration":2.55},{"text":"One, if the -- if the Federal Trade Commission has empower, has not the power, I'm not talking about -- of course you're having that equity jurisdiction in any sense because they're not at court.","start":702.064,"stop":714.548,"duration":12.48},{"text":"I don't know all that talking is next to nothing and got equity jurisdiction because they haven't got any jurisdiction in a judicial sense.","start":714.548,"stop":723.471,"duration":8.92},{"text":"But if the Federal Trade Commission itself has no power which would surprise me and I'm subject to correction (Inaudible), if they haven't got power to stay an order after they find illegality, an order out of fairness to treat competitors in the same condition, the same way.","start":723.471,"stop":744.732,"duration":21.26},{"text":"And there's one question whether the Court has power to qualify an order which the Commission itself has no power.","start":744.732,"stop":751.846,"duration":7.11}]},{"speakerName":"Malcolm I. Frank","textObjs":[{"text":"That's what I was --","start":751.846,"stop":752.193,"duration":0.35}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"If the Commission -- if the Commission has power but doesn't exercise it, that raises a totally different question what the discretionary authority of the Court is to hit into or qualify a discretion exercise in a particular way by the Commission.","start":752.193,"stop":767.737,"duration":15.54}]},{"speakerName":"Malcolm I. Frank","textObjs":[{"text":"Precisely.","start":767.737,"stop":767.825,"duration":0.09}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"And those are very different questions.","start":767.825,"stop":769.49,"duration":1.66}]},{"speakerName":"Malcolm I. Frank","textObjs":[{"text":"That's exactly what I was getting into Justice Frankfurter.","start":769.49,"stop":773.759,"duration":4.27},{"text":"Let's see what the statute says about that power.","start":773.759,"stop":779.238,"duration":5.48},{"text":"Section 21 of the Act, it appears -- I've set it out on page 11 on my brief.","start":779.238,"stop":786.911,"duration":7.67},{"text":"Upon the filing of the application and transcript, the Court shall cause notice to be served on the person and so forth and shall have power to make or enter on the pleading testimony and proceeding set forth in such transcript a decree affirming, modifying or setting aside the order of the Commission under the Board.","start":786.911,"stop":810.402,"duration":23.49},{"text":"Now that phrase, that latter phrase appears three times in that section and in the last place and you will find it on page 12, the jurisdiction of the United States Court of Appeals to enforce, set aside or modified orders of the Commission board shall be exclusive.","start":810.402,"stop":830.51,"duration":20.11},{"text":"Now --","start":830.51,"stop":832.626,"duration":2.12}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"But can the -- can the Court modify or set aside the order of that commission or any other for some reason that hasn't been raised before the Commission itself?","start":832.626,"stop":846.05,"duration":13.42},{"text":"Now, as I understand it, in this case, you did not raise that issue.","start":846.05,"stop":850.032,"duration":3.98},{"text":"You never ask the Commission to -- to withhold its order until it had gone through the same procedure with the rest of the -- of the industry.","start":850.032,"stop":863.231,"duration":13.2},{"text":"But here, you -- you ask the Court to modify or -- or set aside an order of the -- of the Commission on a point that was never raised before the Commission.","start":863.231,"stop":875.826,"duration":12.6}]},{"speakerName":"Malcolm I. Frank","textObjs":[{"text":"That is true because, Mr. Chief Justice, the Federal Trade Commission don't have equitable jurisdiction.","start":875.826,"stop":887.25,"duration":11.42}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, doesn't it have -- I thought you said a little while ago as -- as it may exercise this discretion, as a matter of discretion to withhold such -- such an order until such time this is acted and the rest of the industry.","start":887.25,"stop":904.959,"duration":17.71},{"text":"Did I misunderstand you on that?","start":904.959,"stop":906.763,"duration":1.8}]},{"speakerName":"Malcolm I. Frank","textObjs":[{"text":"Oh, no.","start":906.763,"stop":907.911,"duration":1.15},{"text":"Oh no.","start":907.911,"stop":908.729,"duration":0.82},{"text":"It certainly did.","start":908.729,"stop":909.987,"duration":1.26},{"text":"Now, whether it has power to exercise that discretion, it's a very serious question in my mind and that's what I was getting to when I said a moment ago that the statute says that the jurisdiction of the United States to set aside or modify orders of the Commission is exclusive.","start":909.987,"stop":929.502,"duration":19.51}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Was your doubt so fast it is that you felt inhibited from asking the Commission to -- to exercise that power?","start":929.502,"stop":938.018,"duration":8.52}]},{"speakerName":"Malcolm I. Frank","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Justice Frankfurter, I wasn't in the case at that time.","start":938.018,"stop":940.391,"duration":2.37}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"All right.","start":940.391,"stop":941.04,"duration":0.65},{"text":"Well, the counsel then.","start":941.04,"stop":942.295,"duration":1.25},{"text":"Do you think anybody -- I -- I approved highly, the lawyer is not raising foolish points but since they have that power it wasn't raised, if it was raised.","start":942.295,"stop":954.152,"duration":11.86}]},{"speakerName":"Malcolm I. Frank","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, it was --","start":954.152,"stop":954.21,"duration":0.06}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Can I ask you this?","start":954.21,"stop":955.446,"duration":1.24},{"text":"I ought to know but I don't.","start":955.446,"stop":957.55,"duration":2.1},{"text":"Some statute (Inaudible) say specifically, some of this regulatory statute say specifically you can't raise a point before the Court that wasn't raised before the agency that's a little of the federal power of the Federal Trade Commission Act.","start":957.55,"stop":972.537,"duration":14.99}]},{"speakerName":"Malcolm I. Frank","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, this one does not.","start":972.537,"stop":973.994,"duration":1.46}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"This one does not?","start":973.994,"stop":975.047,"duration":1.05}]},{"speakerName":"Malcolm I. Frank","textObjs":[{"text":"I contend this.","start":975.047,"stop":975.446,"duration":0.4}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"I'm not saying that it isn't -- that impliedly that is a legal point.","start":975.446,"stop":979.059,"duration":3.61},{"text":"I just want to know whether the statute tells that specifically.","start":979.059,"stop":983.091,"duration":4.03}]},{"speakerName":"Malcolm I. Frank","textObjs":[{"text":"I contend that not alone does the Court have the -- the appellate jurisdiction to do this but it has original jurisdiction.","start":983.091,"stop":990.877,"duration":7.79}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, but that doesn't take care of the Chief Justice's point - question, namely, whether a -- a question raise above before the Commission.","start":990.877,"stop":1001.378,"duration":10.5}]},{"speakerName":"Malcolm I. Frank","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, now --","start":1001.378,"stop":1001.588,"duration":0.21}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"But not raised --","start":1001.588,"stop":1003.562,"duration":1.97}]},{"speakerName":"Malcolm I. Frank","textObjs":[{"text":"Here is the way we treated that Mr. Chief Justice.","start":1003.562,"stop":1007.484,"duration":3.92},{"text":"The rules of the Federal Trade Commission provide for a Trade Conference Practice, Trade Practice Conference that is one of the duties delegated to it by Congress.","start":1007.484,"stop":1022.577,"duration":15.09},{"text":"In 1954, April 1954, your petitioner together with other manufacturers as one group petitioned the Federal Trade Commission to hold a -- call a trade practice conference among these manufacturers to correct the very abuses for which they were filing these complaints against mostly smaller companies like ours.","start":1022.577,"stop":1058.82,"duration":36.24},{"text":"Ours is a small company compared to the big ones in the industry.","start":1058.82,"stop":1067.259,"duration":8.44},{"text":"That application has laid there since 1954 and has never been acted upon.","start":1067.259,"stop":1076.018,"duration":8.76},{"text":"In addition to that, that same year, a month or two later, some 200 wholesalers in the industry filed a similar application for a Trade Practice Conference to correct and to go into this very same abuses that the Federal Trade Commission is complaining about because they were receiving discounts and for being liable.","start":1076.018,"stop":1103.012,"duration":26.99},{"text":"They wanted to get it correctly.","start":1103.012,"stop":1105.585,"duration":2.57},{"text":"The Federal Trade Commission has done nothing in that respect.","start":1105.585,"stop":1113.078,"duration":7.49},{"text":"A year later -- a year later, this doesn't appear in the record but it's correct and I'm sure the Federal Trade Commission counsel will not deny it.","start":1113.078,"stop":1124.187,"duration":11.11},{"text":"In December of 1955, Mr. Cassedy, a counsel in this case, wrote to the Chairman of the Commission, calling his attention to the fact that this Trade Practice Conference had been requested by these manufacturers as one group and the wholesaler is another group and that no action had been taken on it and requested and prayed that call this Trade Practice Conference.","start":1124.187,"stop":1156.154,"duration":31.97}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Do you offer -- offer that as an excuse or a reason, let us say, for you're not applying to the Commission to withhold its order until it had gone through the procedure (Voice Overlap) --","start":1156.154,"stop":1168.516,"duration":12.36}]},{"speakerName":"Malcolm I. Frank","textObjs":[{"text":"That's -- that's one of the reasons Mr. Chief Justice and while you say this maybe a play on words.","start":1168.516,"stop":1177.81,"duration":9.29},{"text":"I don't consider it a play on words.","start":1177.81,"stop":1181.75,"duration":3.94},{"text":"Our agencies are either judicial and in the sense they're semi-judicial but they don't have equity jurisdiction.","start":1181.75,"stop":1192.408,"duration":10.66},{"text":"Whether or not the Federal Trade Commission, when they entered into an agreement with the attorney's, for these cosmetics people to hold up any action until final decree was entered in the Elizabeth Arden cases so that they can all work together and then work under the same rules recognizing the competitive disadvantage.","start":1192.408,"stop":1221.774,"duration":29.37},{"text":"It is a serious question in my mind whether they have that right.","start":1221.774,"stop":1230.426,"duration":8.65},{"text":"Here's what they did in the lumber industry, in the Algoma case.","start":1230.426,"stop":1233.797,"duration":3.37}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, I thought Justice Douglas pointed out that there was a distinction in that Arden case from this one.","start":1233.797,"stop":1243.942,"duration":10.14},{"text":"I thought he pointed out that in that case, they have tried these cases in the -- that were being -- being held awaiting the disposition of one -- of one case.","start":1243.942,"stop":1255.698,"duration":11.76}]},{"speakerName":"Malcolm I. Frank","textObjs":[{"text":"My recollection is all the cases had not been tried.","start":1255.698,"stop":1259.468,"duration":3.77},{"text":"Elizabeth Arden was the first one tried.","start":1259.468,"stop":1261.824,"duration":2.36}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes.","start":1261.824,"stop":1262.331,"duration":0.51}]},{"speakerName":"Malcolm I. Frank","textObjs":[{"text":"And the others were being proceeded and Elizabeth Arden was being appealed.","start":1262.331,"stop":1268.028,"duration":5.7}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes.","start":1268.028,"stop":1268.266,"duration":0.24}]},{"speakerName":"Malcolm I. Frank","textObjs":[{"text":"And on the final appeal, the agreement was again entered into that it would not be enforced against Elizabeth Arden until a final decree had been entered in the last of the eight cosmetic cases.","start":1268.266,"stop":1285.477,"duration":17.21}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Arden, I beg your pardon.","start":1285.477,"stop":1287.9,"duration":2.42},{"text":"Mr. Frank, lawyers can try two lawsuits at the same time if he's skillful enough.","start":1287.9,"stop":1294.708,"duration":6.81},{"text":"So I can see that you don't have to choose between two positions, but do you take either or both namely that the power -- that the Trade Commission has not the power to stay it's order and that relief for that must be had from the Court or you say alternatively, if it has the power and doesn't exercise it.","start":1294.708,"stop":1319.48,"duration":24.77},{"text":"It's such an abusive discretion that the Court can rectify that abuse.","start":1319.48,"stop":1324.757,"duration":5.28}]},{"speakerName":"Malcolm I. Frank","textObjs":[{"text":"I would say --","start":1324.757,"stop":1325.755,"duration":1}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Or you take some other position still?","start":1325.755,"stop":1328.334,"duration":2.58}]},{"speakerName":"Malcolm I. Frank","textObjs":[{"text":"May I put it this way, sir.","start":1328.334,"stop":1331.306,"duration":2.97},{"text":"I would say that the Federal Trade Commission has power to make effective the date of an order anytime that it see fit it chooses.","start":1331.306,"stop":1344.948,"duration":13.64},{"text":"There is no question about that.","start":1344.948,"stop":1347.002,"duration":2.05},{"text":"They can have the power to relate a decree effective a year from next Tuesday if they want to or eight years from the next Tuesday if they want to.","start":1347.002,"stop":1360.224,"duration":13.22},{"text":"But I say that when a record shows as this one shows even though a request is not made, there is no waiver of the right.","start":1360.224,"stop":1375.961,"duration":15.74},{"text":"There is no waiver of the right.","start":1375.961,"stop":1381.449,"duration":5.49},{"text":"Unquestionably, not alone has the Court of Appeals, the exclusive jurisdiction to modify, affirm or set aside a Federal Trade Commission order.","start":1381.449,"stop":1394.696,"duration":13.25},{"text":"It is my opinion Your Honors that the Constitution of the United States gives the Court a reasonable equitable jurisdiction in any case presented to it at any time.","start":1394.696,"stop":1410.871,"duration":16.18},{"text":"Chief Justice Marshall said so in Osborn against United States Bank, decided by this Court many, many years ago.","start":1410.871,"stop":1426.472,"duration":15.6},{"text":"In Old Colony Trust Company against Commission of Internal Revenue, that was a case where the question was referred to this Court referring to a decision of the Board of Tax Appeals and referred to Article 3 of the Constitution.","start":1426.472,"stop":1450.101,"duration":23.63},{"text":"Article 3 of the Constitution as you know says that the judicial power extends the whole cases in law and equity arising under the Constitution and the laws of the United States.","start":1450.101,"stop":1461.505,"duration":11.4}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, then it's your position that to enforce an order to stay, to cease and desist a violation of the Federal Trade Commission Act against a particular business would be so inequitable if the same order conceded is -- the same order violated by competitors of the petitioner and not also ordered to be stay just to be ceased and desisted, so inequitable to the Court of Appeals to which -- which has the reviewing power of such an order or as an exercise of its inherent or granted equity powers grant such a stay, is that your position?","start":1461.505,"stop":1510.757,"duration":49.25}]},{"speakerName":"Malcolm I. Frank","textObjs":[{"text":"That is the position especially where the record shows that this is a standard practice in the industry.","start":1510.757,"stop":1520.236,"duration":9.48},{"text":"We are in effect, Your Honors, made legal guinea pigs.","start":1520.236,"stop":1527.739,"duration":7.5},{"text":"We're a little concerned in a two and a half billion dollar industry.","start":1527.739,"stop":1532.138,"duration":4.4},{"text":"Our volume in 1952 was a little under 5,000,000.","start":1532.138,"stop":1539.299,"duration":7.16},{"text":"We're a drop in the bucket in the big industry like this.","start":1539.299,"stop":1546.812,"duration":7.51},{"text":"We can't compete with other concerns.","start":1546.812,"stop":1549.804,"duration":2.99},{"text":"We lose customers weekly and daily to our competitors who are still offering volume discounts who have not been proceeded against.","start":1549.804,"stop":1559.372,"duration":9.57},{"text":"When they go and say “Well, we can give you a cheaper price.”","start":1559.372,"stop":1564.46,"duration":5.09}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Frank do you have -- do you have any authorities in this field which -- which hold that the Court of Appeals can modify an order of the Federal Trade Commission on a point that was not raised or could not -- or could not have been raised or that was not raised before the Commission itself?","start":1564.46,"stop":1595.067,"duration":30.61}]},{"speakerName":"Malcolm I. Frank","textObjs":[{"text":"I know of no case on that point offhand Mr. Justice, but I do know this, that this Court held in Old Colony Trust Company against Commissioner of Internal Revenue that on the petitioner finding of an executive or administrative tribunal, it was not important whether the proceeding was originally began by administrative or executive determination if when it came to the Court and that's the Court of Appeals.","start":1595.067,"stop":1640.896,"duration":45.83},{"text":"If -- when it came to the Court, it call for the exercise of the judicial power of the Court upon which jurisdiction was conferred by the law.","start":1640.896,"stop":1649.844,"duration":8.95},{"text":"And then in that same case, this Court said, at page 723, judge, the Court further held that the jurisdiction and that cause was like that of Circuit Courts of Appeal in review of orders of the Federal Trade Commission and cited in support the Eastman Kodak case and the Silver against the Federal Trade Commission case.","start":1649.844,"stop":1672.862,"duration":23.02},{"text":"Now, Courts of Appeals in the Second Circuit have done it.","start":1672.862,"stop":1677.79,"duration":4.93},{"text":"Courts of Appeals in the Seventh Circuit have done it.","start":1677.79,"stop":1681.539,"duration":3.75},{"text":"Courts of Appeals in the Sixth Circuit have done it and Court of Appeals in my own Eighth Circuit did it, notwithstanding Justice Whittaker's overruling of it.","start":1681.539,"stop":1692.934,"duration":11.39},{"text":"They did it in the Chamber of Commerce case that's cited in the brief.","start":1692.934,"stop":1697.872,"duration":4.94},{"text":"Now, whether it's a question --","start":1697.872,"stop":1701.144,"duration":3.27}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Do you know --","start":1701.144,"stop":1701.621,"duration":0.48}]},{"speakerName":"Malcolm I. Frank","textObjs":[{"text":"-- we ought to raise it first down there or whether we ought to raise it originally in here in the Old Colony case, it's says it has the original jurisdiction in the Court.","start":1701.621,"stop":1713.346,"duration":11.72}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Do you know -- do you know Mr. Frank if in those cases that you have just cited, the -- the petitioner did or did not request the Commission to withhold its order.","start":1713.346,"stop":1728.06,"duration":14.71},{"text":"I don't know myself.","start":1728.06,"stop":1730.016,"duration":1.96}]},{"speakerName":"Malcolm I. Frank","textObjs":[{"text":"No, the only one that I know of where the Commission was asked to withhold its order was in the Niehoff case which is to be argued right after mine.","start":1730.016,"stop":1741.142,"duration":11.13}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes.","start":1741.142,"stop":1741.519,"duration":0.38}]},{"speakerName":"Malcolm I. Frank","textObjs":[{"text":"In the other cases, I don't think it was raised.","start":1741.519,"stop":1745.202,"duration":3.68}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Frank, may I ask you one more question.","start":1745.202,"stop":1747.386,"duration":2.18}]},{"speakerName":"Malcolm I. Frank","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, sir.","start":1747.386,"stop":1748.552,"duration":1.17}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Suppose the request -- a request for a stay of the enforcement of an order against competitor one until competitors -- the rest of them dealt with, were made before the Commission.","start":1748.552,"stop":1764.485,"duration":15.93},{"text":"And suppose the Commission considered it and after hearing arguments pro and con, decided against such a stay.","start":1764.485,"stop":1775.04,"duration":10.56},{"text":"But it's considered and gave reason for denying.","start":1775.04,"stop":1779.96,"duration":4.92},{"text":"I can think of administrative process and so on and so on, would that be a different -- would that present a different case than where as in the Niehoff case, a request is made and denied.","start":1779.96,"stop":1795.349,"duration":15.39}]},{"speakerName":"Malcolm I. Frank","textObjs":[{"text":"I think so.","start":1795.349,"stop":1795.527,"duration":0.18}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Would that make any difference?","start":1795.527,"stop":1797.062,"duration":1.53}]},{"speakerName":"Malcolm I. Frank","textObjs":[{"text":"Very much so.","start":1797.062,"stop":1797.838,"duration":0.78},{"text":"I'll --","start":1797.838,"stop":1798.118,"duration":0.28}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"But if it makes different --","start":1798.118,"stop":1799.024,"duration":0.91}]},{"speakerName":"Malcolm I. Frank","textObjs":[{"text":"I'll tell you why.","start":1799.024,"stop":1800.302,"duration":1.28}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"All right.","start":1800.302,"stop":1800.45,"duration":0.15}]},{"speakerName":"Malcolm I. Frank","textObjs":[{"text":"In my opinion, this Federal Trade Commission can't make a finding of fact on something on which it has no jurisdiction.","start":1800.45,"stop":1810.922,"duration":10.47}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, but you just --","start":1810.922,"stop":1811.599,"duration":0.68}]},{"speakerName":"Malcolm I. Frank","textObjs":[{"text":"It would have to make a finding of fact and the -- the Government's brief says that there's no finding of fact made on it.","start":1811.599,"stop":1820.028,"duration":8.43},{"text":"They can't make a finding of fact on something that's beyond their jurisdiction.","start":1820.028,"stop":1823.639,"duration":3.61}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"But I -- I -- pardon me because I thought you agree that the Commission could state an order of invalidity, didn't you say that?","start":1823.639,"stop":1832.963,"duration":9.32}]},{"speakerName":"Malcolm I. Frank","textObjs":[{"text":"I said that but Your Honor said they made findings of fact and state that there are reasons for it.","start":1832.963,"stop":1838.113,"duration":5.15},{"text":"There's a distinction between the two.","start":1838.113,"stop":1840.566,"duration":2.45},{"text":"If the Federal Trade Commission had come out totally and said “We're going to make this order effective when we get the balance of the industry in line.”","start":1840.566,"stop":1853.89,"duration":13.32},{"text":"That's one thing.","start":1853.89,"stop":1855.509,"duration":1.62},{"text":"But if the Federal Trade Commission come out and says “For the reason that so and so and for the reason that so and so, we don't consider this evidence sufficient and makes findings of fact.”","start":1855.509,"stop":1866.091,"duration":10.58},{"text":"I say they haven't got jurisdiction to make those findings of fact.","start":1866.091,"stop":1868.656,"duration":2.57}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, then they must always grant a stay if there are competitors in the field according to your argument.","start":1868.656,"stop":1875.095,"duration":6.44}]},{"speakerName":"Malcolm I. Frank","textObjs":[{"text":"No, sir.","start":1875.095,"stop":1875.634,"duration":0.54}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"But if not then --","start":1875.634,"stop":1876.562,"duration":0.93}]},{"speakerName":"Malcolm I. Frank","textObjs":[{"text":"Not unless the record justifies that it is a standard practice throughout the industry.","start":1876.562,"stop":1883.016,"duration":6.45},{"text":"I don't mean that it should be done indiscriminately.","start":1883.016,"stop":1885.808,"duration":2.79},{"text":"Here, it's standard practice in the industry.","start":1885.808,"stop":1888.932,"duration":3.12},{"text":"There's no denial of that fact that there are rebates and discounts on piston rings and replacement parts in one form or another throughout the industry.","start":1888.932,"stop":1898.8,"duration":9.87},{"text":"It's just the same as years ago when you walk and -- when my daddy used to walk into the drugstore and bought a cigar and he could buy one for 10 cents or he could buy three for a quarter.","start":1898.8,"stop":1911.301,"duration":12.5},{"text":"That's the cost.","start":1911.301,"stop":1911.98,"duration":0.68},{"text":"It was quantity.","start":1911.98,"stop":1913.545,"duration":1.57},{"text":"Or when I can remember very well, a relative of mine was in business and when he bought thread from the Spool Cotton Company.","start":1913.545,"stop":1924.012,"duration":10.47},{"text":"The more thread you bought in a year, the bigger credit bonus you got at the end of the year.","start":1924.012,"stop":1928.952,"duration":4.94},{"text":"Quantity discounts are in grand in the industry of commerce in almost any line that you want to talk about.","start":1928.952,"stop":1937.643,"duration":8.69},{"text":"And it's awful hard, it's awful hard to just uproot it and say to this one and this one you can't do it anymore while it takes years to get the rest of that industry in line.","start":1937.643,"stop":1954.772,"duration":17.13},{"text":"In the meantime, we've lost customers.","start":1954.772,"stop":1958.792,"duration":4.02},{"text":"The Federal Trade Commission says “Well, you've got a remedy, you can sue them.”","start":1958.792,"stop":1962.562,"duration":3.77},{"text":"Well, of course we can sue them but that don't get us our customers back and money damages wouldn't replace the lost of those customers that are gone from us.","start":1962.562,"stop":1975.446,"duration":12.88},{"text":"There's just one more thing if I may indulge.","start":1975.446,"stop":1978.697,"duration":3.25},{"text":"The attorney general with reference to price, the attorney general's committee to investigate the antitrust back said in one paragraph and it's referred to in the brief and it's very important to me and I think to you is that competition where it's keen and a reduction in price in order to meet a rival's price if it's forbidden, forbidden is reductio ad absurdum.","start":1978.697,"stop":2019.831,"duration":41.13},{"text":"That's it.","start":2019.831,"stop":2021.077,"duration":1.25},{"text":"Thank you very much and I would like very much to have this Court not tell the Trade Commission what to do in it's discretion but to stay this order until the Federal Trade Commission can either exercise its discretion in calling a trade conference or bring these cases against our competitors to a conclusion.","start":2021.077,"stop":2045.902,"duration":24.83},{"text":"Thank you very much.","start":2045.902,"stop":2048.155,"duration":2.25}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Kintner.","start":2048.155,"stop":2050.551,"duration":2.4}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"May it please the Court.","start":2050.551,"stop":2057.853,"duration":7.3},{"text":"Counsel has made reference to the cosmetics case, the fact that the Federal Trade Commission entered into an understanding that the Court's decision in the Elizabeth Arden case would bind the parties with respect to other pending proceedings which were at various stages of the administrative process.","start":2057.853,"stop":2082.926,"duration":25.07},{"text":"The Commission exercised it's discretion as in its law enforcement capacity in entering into this understanding.","start":2082.926,"stop":2091.797,"duration":8.87},{"text":"It did subsequently dismissed six -- those six pending cases and attempted -- and did have a Trade Practice Conference to suggest rules of conduct for the parties and it is a fact that after the Trade Practice Conference and after they'd all signed the pledge card, the Commission found it necessary to institute an industry wide investigation of the cosmetics industry.","start":2091.797,"stop":2118.858,"duration":27.06},{"text":"It issued complaints against three of those against whom it had dismissed the cases and the other three had signed the pledge cards.","start":2118.858,"stop":2133.418,"duration":14.56},{"text":"This illustrates graphically, I think, the fact that these voluntary procedures of the Commission indeed of any law enforcement agency are no better than scraps of paper unless they are backed up by firm enforcement of the laws.","start":2133.418,"stop":2155.824,"duration":22.41},{"text":"It is true that there was an application for a Trade Practice Conference in 1954 with respect to certain segments of this industry.","start":2155.824,"stop":2165.741,"duration":9.92},{"text":"It is also true since we've gone beyond the record that the Department of Justice subjected to the holding of that Trade Practice Conference because it then had under investigation certain segments of the industry and it was not -- and it is not the department's policy nor that of the Commission to settle by Trade Practice Conferences, matters which are in litigation or where substantial amount of investigative authority has been exercised and substantial amounts of the public's money spent to investigate the practice or where there is real controversy with respect to the legality or illegality of the practices in question.","start":2165.741,"stop":2210.367,"duration":44.63},{"text":"It is true that there was another application in 1957, but these cases were then in litigation.","start":2210.367,"stop":2217.411,"duration":7.04},{"text":"The Commission had filed 16 price discrimination complaints in this particular industry, the Automotive Replacement Parts Industry.","start":2217.411,"stop":2229.317,"duration":11.91}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"The Commission -- I'm sorry, the Commission had done what?","start":2229.317,"stop":2232.161,"duration":2.84}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"Had filed 16 companion cases or two-way cases in this industry.","start":2232.161,"stop":2238.035,"duration":5.87}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Could -- could such -- such an inquiry or could such complaints be considered in a single proceeding to where the I.C.C.often brings before it the vast inquiry?","start":2238.035,"stop":2251.457,"duration":13.42}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"In my judgment sir, it would be utterly impossible because in price discrimination cases, each respondent has certain defenses, the cost defense, the defense of good -- of meeting competition; the question indeed in the first instance of whether he is engaged in Interstate Commerce.","start":2251.457,"stop":2274.167,"duration":22.71},{"text":"And finally, the all important question which makes these cases so complicated and so lengthy in many instances, the question of whether or not there has been the requisite injury to competition or the tendency to -- toward monopoly required by the statute.","start":2274.167,"stop":2291.72,"duration":17.55}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"You impliedly by that answer did not deny the suggestion or the claim that in fact there was uniform trade practice here which governed all those in it.","start":2291.72,"stop":2307.557,"duration":15.84},{"text":"You deny that.","start":2307.557,"stop":2308.304,"duration":0.75}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"To the extent that there were certain pricing practices being engaged in by certain segments of the industry.","start":2308.304,"stop":2318.256,"duration":9.95},{"text":"Counsel is right.","start":2318.256,"stop":2319.424,"duration":1.17},{"text":"But it is not necessarily true that all of these pricing practices of all members of the industry were violative of the law.","start":2319.424,"stop":2329.675,"duration":10.25}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"No, but as to those -- as to practices that were uniformly though not all the practices that you might look into, but as to practices where there was uniformity in the industry, does the Commission or the Commission enable to bring the whole industry before it and order -- one fell order to outlaw in such a uniform practice.","start":2329.675,"stop":2351.607,"duration":21.93}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"The Commission has not found it possible Mr. Justice Frankfurter to do this.","start":2351.607,"stop":2357.625,"duration":6.02},{"text":"If it were able, it would have exercised its administrative discretion to do so.","start":2357.625,"stop":2363.98,"duration":6.36}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Tell me why as to the admission that you've made.","start":2363.98,"stop":2366.915,"duration":2.93},{"text":"I mean the statement you made a minute ago.","start":2366.915,"stop":2370.346,"duration":3.43},{"text":"There were certain practices that were uniformed.","start":2370.346,"stop":2373.101,"duration":2.76},{"text":"What is the -- what are the administrative pampering that this does that prevent those practices from being dealt with in -- in a comprehensive, in an all industry comprehending order?","start":2373.101,"stop":2386.046,"duration":12.94}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"The fact that each respondent has a cost justification defense under the statute available to him.","start":2386.046,"stop":2393.769,"duration":7.72},{"text":"The cost of one respondent may not be the cost of another.","start":2393.769,"stop":2398.009,"duration":4.24},{"text":"Each respondent under the statute has a possible defense of good faith meeting of the competition.","start":2398.009,"stop":2406.475,"duration":8.47},{"text":"And in this industry, there were seven -- there were approximately 75 lines of products, each product in many instances broken down into sub lines with literally thousands of parts within some particular line.","start":2406.475,"stop":2425.97,"duration":19.49}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Or what -- on what basis did you say that Mr. Frank's statement was true as to some practices?","start":2425.97,"stop":2432.537,"duration":6.57}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"Only to the extent that some of his competitors, we believe, because we've issued 16 complaints in this industry, do use annual volume discounts either rebating in -- at the end of the year in cash or in merchandise.","start":2432.537,"stop":2451.478,"duration":18.94}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Does the establishment of that uniform practice require individualized, complicated inquiry as to each business?","start":2451.478,"stop":2460.045,"duration":8.57}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"We certainly do not think so, Your Honor.","start":2460.045,"stop":2461.852,"duration":1.81}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"So that -- there you could have a single -- I'm not saying that makes a difference.","start":2461.852,"stop":2465.583,"duration":3.73},{"text":"I'm just trying to find out what the administrative problems are which may make a difference in what courts do or allowed to do.","start":2465.583,"stop":2472.028,"duration":6.44}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"The problem might graphically be expressed by -- by this example that A and B compete with C in this industry, but C competes with D and E.","start":2472.028,"stop":2486.023,"duration":14},{"text":"There would be a never ending succession of competitors, one of it competes with another and then with two others in such a proceeding.","start":2486.023,"stop":2493.806,"duration":7.78},{"text":"The case -- the proceeding would never end.","start":2493.806,"stop":2496.231,"duration":2.43},{"text":"There would never be an order issued, an effective order by the Commission.","start":2496.231,"stop":2500.877,"duration":4.65},{"text":"And as to the practices of each of these competitors, there would come into play the defenses of the Act and above all the question of whether or not each pricing practice of each have the requisite adverse effects as required by the statute upon the competition.","start":2500.877,"stop":2521.407,"duration":20.53}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"But are you saying -- are you saying -- this is what I gathered from what you've said that although it may appear on a surface, on a façade view that there is a uniform practice in an industry concerning so many -- anywhere from two or more many competitors, although it may appear there is a single uniformed industry wide practice.","start":2521.407,"stop":2546.463,"duration":25.06},{"text":"As a matter of fact, that apparently single uniformed practice is so individualized that you cannot do it otherwise in case by case.","start":2546.463,"stop":2556.882,"duration":10.42},{"text":"Is that what you're saying?","start":2556.882,"stop":2557.83,"duration":0.95}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, sir.","start":2557.83,"stop":2558.239,"duration":0.41},{"text":"Now, there had been instances, notably, the lead pigment industry and the cement industry where the -- the factors in the industry were tied together in a price fixing conspiracy or combination where their practices were uniform.","start":2558.239,"stop":2576.349,"duration":18.11},{"text":"There, the Commission has exercised its discretion in issuing a price discrimination count with respect to the -- the conspiracy portion of the complaint and has cleaned up the industry in the one proceeding.","start":2576.349,"stop":2593.366,"duration":17.02},{"text":"But this is not the case in the Automotive Replacement Parts Industry.","start":2593.366,"stop":2598.464,"duration":5.1}]},{"speakerName":"UNKNOWN","textObjs":[{"text":"Are there any -- are there any of instances where you failed to file a complaint against the -- what might be fairly called as the Moog -- any of Moog's competitors.","start":2598.464,"stop":2615.068,"duration":16.6},{"text":"Have you proceeded against the whole industry --","start":2615.068,"stop":2616.363,"duration":1.29}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"We have --","start":2616.363,"stop":2617.052,"duration":0.69}]},{"speakerName":"UNKNOWN","textObjs":[{"text":"-- for this class of -- for this class of violation?","start":2617.052,"stop":2619.896,"duration":2.84}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"As we have collected evidence and as it has appeared to the Commission that the statute may be violated.","start":2619.896,"stop":2627.206,"duration":7.31},{"text":"The Commission has proceeded to issue its complaint and has proceeded to hold its administrative hearings as speedily as possible.","start":2627.206,"stop":2636.956,"duration":9.75}]},{"speakerName":"UNKNOWN","textObjs":[{"text":"What did you find happens when you litigate one of these cases?","start":2636.956,"stop":2640.247,"duration":3.29},{"text":"You've got talk of consent decrees coming in or do you have to litigate them all?","start":2640.247,"stop":2643.651,"duration":3.4}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"Interestingly enough Mr. Justice Harlan, one of respond -- of petitioners, principal competitor's sealed power has signed a consent settlement with the Federal Trade Commission.","start":2643.651,"stop":2659.578,"duration":15.93}]},{"speakerName":"UNKNOWN","textObjs":[{"text":"The same scope that the non-consent decree here (Voice Overlap) --","start":2659.578,"stop":2662.55,"duration":2.97}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, sir.","start":2662.55,"stop":2662.947,"duration":0.4}]},{"speakerName":"UNKNOWN","textObjs":[{"text":"-- the story that you presented?","start":2662.947,"stop":2664.504,"duration":1.56}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, sir.","start":2664.504,"stop":2665.991,"duration":1.49},{"text":"We -- we expect and can only expect when the Commission issues complaints against individuals in an industry charged with violating the law that once the principles or practices therein involved have been litigated and passed upon by the courts that others in the industry similarly situated will fall into line.","start":2665.991,"stop":2692.341,"duration":26.35},{"text":"If they do not of course, the Commission must proceed to investigate as the practices of competitors are called to its attention and to issue complaints and hold hearings within the limits of his -- of its budget.","start":2692.341,"stop":2707.458,"duration":15.12},{"text":"For example, here, during a nine year period, 25% of the price discrimination complaints issued by the Federal Trade Commission, during that nine-year period have been issued in this particular industry.","start":2707.458,"stop":2725.263,"duration":17.8},{"text":"The Commission has moved vigorously to stand proud, practices which it believes are unlawful in the industry.","start":2725.263,"stop":2732.487,"duration":7.22}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Did the -- did the proceeding which resulted in the order in the Moog case, in this case, start by some private complaint or on the Commission's initiation?","start":2732.487,"stop":2744.893,"duration":12.41}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"Now that is a very interesting question and requires some background detail at this point.","start":2744.893,"stop":2756.597,"duration":11.7},{"text":"The Commission's attention was invited to the fact that the jobbers who are the customers or petitioner here and others similarly situated were that certain jobbers were receiving better prices than others because those jobbers belong to buying groups.","start":2756.597,"stop":2778.16,"duration":21.56},{"text":"The buying groups were able to secure from petitioner and others far better prices than the individual members were able to secure in their own negotiations.","start":2778.16,"stop":2795.893,"duration":17.73},{"text":"Members of the buying groups bought individually.","start":2795.893,"stop":2799.354,"duration":3.46},{"text":"They individually ordered.","start":2799.354,"stop":2801.28,"duration":1.93},{"text":"Shipments were made individually, but they were billed through the buying group, a mere book keeping device in our view to avoid the law.","start":2801.28,"stop":2814.042,"duration":12.76},{"text":"The situation is graphically illustrated by the Dallas situation.","start":2814.042,"stop":2818.902,"duration":4.86},{"text":"There were six customers, our petitioner.","start":2818.902,"stop":2823.518,"duration":4.62},{"text":"Four of them belong to jobbing groups and secured discounts of 12% to 15%.","start":2823.518,"stop":2830.153,"duration":6.63},{"text":"Two did not belong.","start":2830.153,"stop":2832.416,"duration":2.26},{"text":"One jobber didn't get any discount.","start":2832.416,"stop":2835.959,"duration":3.54},{"text":"The other jobber who was the largest one in the area got 7.29% discount.","start":2835.959,"stop":2842.479,"duration":6.52},{"text":"And I invite the Court's attention to the fact that the record indicates that this industry, the jobbing end of it, operates on a 4% or less net profit basis, so that the discount that the largest jobber was not receiving simply because he didn't belong to this bookkeeping transaction.","start":2842.479,"stop":2870.274,"duration":27.8},{"text":"It's terribly important to him in his survival as an independent businessman and it was because the Commission found that these buying groups, these bookkeeping devices were pervading the industry that it moved against the manufacturers who were according the prices to the buying groups.","start":2870.274,"stop":2891.875,"duration":21.6}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"We'll not take that thing -- could the whole -- all those who are pursuing that practice could they not be brought into a single proceeding?","start":2891.875,"stop":2900.896,"duration":9.02}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"We don't think so, Your Honor.","start":2900.896,"stop":2903.391,"duration":2.49},{"text":"First place, we don't believe that all of the manufacturers in the industry are engaged in the same pricing practice.","start":2903.391,"stop":2911.159,"duration":7.77}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Those who did -- those who did.","start":2911.159,"stop":2912.097,"duration":0.94},{"text":"I'm trying to -- I'm drawing the legal (Voice Overlap) --","start":2912.097,"stop":2916.559,"duration":4.46}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"As to those who --","start":2916.559,"stop":2917.495,"duration":0.94}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"-- get understanding of what the administrative does and why does it and what it has to do and what it does not have to do for effective administration.","start":2917.495,"stop":2925.772,"duration":8.28}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"As to those in the industry who are engaged in according annual, volume, discount, rebates based upon cumulative purchases during the year as to those.","start":2925.772,"stop":2942.47,"duration":16.7},{"text":"Each in a proceeding would have here a separate defense that his price is valid because he is simply according a differential based upon the cost of doing business or that he accords this price differential based upon the fact that he's meeting the competition of a competitor in a certain area.","start":2942.47,"stop":2965.775,"duration":23.31}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, I don't understand from what you said that any of that would be irrelevant to a situation where as a matter of bookkeeping, a fellow gets the discount because he belongs to a buying group and the other fellow who doesn't stands out against the buying group doesn't get the discount.","start":2965.775,"stop":2981.168,"duration":15.39},{"text":"What is that -- what kind of a defense the difference in cost be if that's the reason of the differential?","start":2981.168,"stop":2986.176,"duration":5.01}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"We have proceeded against the buying groups.","start":2986.176,"stop":2988.459,"duration":2.28},{"text":"We have some 10 complaints pending against the buying groups or receiving the -- the unlawful price discriminations.","start":2988.459,"stop":3000.604,"duration":12.14},{"text":"They in turn of course have their defenses.","start":3000.604,"stop":3004.225,"duration":3.62},{"text":"But as to each of these respondents, they would have each their various defenses and then there would be the question of whether or not individually they were entering competition and each would have varying lines of competitors.","start":3004.225,"stop":3023.827,"duration":19.6},{"text":"They sell different products in this industry and each has a variety of competitors, some common and some not common one or the other.","start":3023.827,"stop":3032.609,"duration":8.78}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr.-- may I ask you this Mr. Kintner.","start":3032.609,"stop":3034.805,"duration":2.2},{"text":"Apart from the Elizabeth Arden case, does the Commission sometimes stay its order to cease and desist?","start":3034.805,"stop":3043.811,"duration":9.01},{"text":"And if so, on what ground does it stay if -- if they are capable of generalization?","start":3043.811,"stop":3049.171,"duration":5.36}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"The Commission uses its administrative discretion in practically and I believe all orders that it issues to require compliance within 60 days of a forthwith order and the courts have sustained scores of such orders and have made it a part of the Court's judgment that compliance shall be had within 60 days.","start":3049.171,"stop":3077.21,"duration":28.04},{"text":"Once an order of the Commission has been issued in a case of this character and has been affirmed by Court of Appeals, there comes the arduous process of securing compliance with that order.","start":3077.21,"stop":3093.536,"duration":16.33},{"text":"First, there is the 60-day waiting period during which respondent may adjust its business and must at least convince the Commission of its good faith and effort to comply with the order.","start":3093.536,"stop":3107.882,"duration":14.35},{"text":"The division of compliance which is lodged in my office has authority on its own motion and without reference to the Federal Trade Commission to grant an additional 60 days during which respondent may use good faith in attempting to adjust his business practices.","start":3107.882,"stop":3125.771,"duration":17.89},{"text":"And then after all that and assuming that respondent has not satisfied the Commission that it's using good faith and attempting to comply with the order, after all that, the Commission then enters into the second stage of the proceeding.","start":3125.771,"stop":3142.103,"duration":16.33},{"text":"It goes to a Court of Appeals and phrase an enforcement of the order.","start":3142.103,"stop":3147.151,"duration":5.05},{"text":"And even that doesn't end the procedure.","start":3147.151,"stop":3149.953,"duration":2.8},{"text":"The Commission must detect a third violation and must go again to the Court of Appeals and enforce the order to the Court's contempt power.","start":3149.953,"stop":3160.028,"duration":10.07}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"That's all worked out administratively.","start":3160.028,"stop":3162.134,"duration":2.11},{"text":"I mean that -- the process which you've just outlined has been evolved --","start":3162.134,"stop":3165.593,"duration":3.46}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"It is.","start":3165.593,"stop":3166.362,"duration":0.77},{"text":"It has --","start":3166.362,"stop":3166.47,"duration":0.11}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"-- with the help of the Commission.","start":3166.47,"stop":3167.606,"duration":1.14}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"-- it has been evolved following this Court's decision in the Ruberoid case, 343 U.S. 470 at page 476 where this Court held that such procedures so far as the second and third stage, were required by the statute.","start":3167.606,"stop":3185.842,"duration":18.24}]},{"speakerName":"UNKNOWN","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible)","start":3185.842,"stop":3191.341,"duration":5.5}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"In -- the instance here, the two cases have -- have been in gestation nine years, two and a half of those before the Court's --","start":3191.341,"stop":3201.4,"duration":10.06}]},{"speakerName":"UNKNOWN","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible)","start":3201.4,"stop":3207.03,"duration":5.63}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"I don't think it's entirely typical, but the Commission finds that next to the price fixing industry wide price fixing cases that these two-way cases under the Robinson-Patman law are very difficult and lengthy if respondent wishes to try out all of the defenses available to it and all of the issues which may properly be examined under the law.","start":3207.03,"stop":3234.504,"duration":27.47},{"text":"We must rely upon establishing precedent and then bringing the rest of the industry into compliance.","start":3234.504,"stop":3240.526,"duration":6.02}]},{"speakerName":"UNKNOWN","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible)","start":3240.526,"stop":3245.117,"duration":4.59}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"That -- I would go further than that and say that the case would never end.","start":3245.117,"stop":3250.085,"duration":4.97},{"text":"The possibilities for litigation are such that half the antitrust part would be gainfully employed for half a century.","start":3250.085,"stop":3259.724,"duration":9.64},{"text":"That is the result which the Commission devoutly does not seek part.","start":3259.724,"stop":3269.131,"duration":9.41}]}]},{"transcriptTitle":"Oral Argument, Part 2: Moog Industries, Inc. v. FTC - January 14, 1958 (77)","transcriptLink":"https://apps.oyez.org/player/#/warren6/oral_argument_audio/13485","transcript":[{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"You may proceed Mr. Kintner.","start":0,"stop":7.832,"duration":7.83}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"May it please the Court.","start":7.832,"stop":12.778,"duration":4.95},{"text":"In replying to questions of Mr. Justice Frankfurter, I think it might be relevant to point out concerning the pricing practices of the petitioner here.","start":12.778,"stop":30.466,"duration":17.69},{"text":"That the pricing practice complained of and which it alleges is common to the industry, was only superficially common to substantially -- substantial portions of the industry.","start":30.466,"stop":46.642,"duration":16.18},{"text":"For instance, in its own three principal lines, the respondent has a different price, maximum price with respect to each of those lines, 0% to 19% in its coil line, 0% to 15% in its leaf spring line and 0% to 20% in its piston line.","start":46.642,"stop":84.756,"duration":38.11},{"text":"This Court in the -- I'm turning very briefly to cases which we think govern in this instance.","start":84.756,"stop":95.13,"duration":10.37},{"text":"This Court in the case of U.S. versus Wabash Railroad said -- had this to say, the suppression of abuses resulting from violations would be rendered practically impossible if the Commission referring to the I.C.C. were required to suppress all simultaneously or none.","start":95.13,"stop":117.296,"duration":22.17},{"text":"Section 12 (1), imposes on the Commission, the duty to enforce the provisions of the Act.","start":117.296,"stop":122.638,"duration":5.34},{"text":"That duty would hardly be performed if the Commission were to define -- decline to enforce it, against one because it could not at the same time enforce it against all.","start":122.638,"stop":136.217,"duration":13.58},{"text":"And many years later, Judge Medina graphically following that line of reasoning in a Clayton Act proceeding Section 3 case said that preliminarily, it's been noted, that potential or even probable adverse effects on petitioner's business alone is not sufficient basis for withholding injunctive relief, where we to hold otherwise, we would quite effectively draw the teeth of Section 3 and the antitrust laws generally.","start":136.217,"stop":169.137,"duration":32.92},{"text":"It appears self evident that any provision upon behavior which tightens competition will necessarily endure to the immediate economic disadvantage of the individual or business organization engaged in that behavior.","start":169.137,"stop":189.876,"duration":20.74},{"text":"Essentially, the problem raised here in this appeal is one that is common not only to the Federal Trade Commission's submission of law enforcement but is a common -- a problem common to all law enforcement.","start":189.876,"stop":211.119,"duration":21.24},{"text":"It was as ever been does that those charge to a violation of the -- of the law say to the administrator or the person engaged in enforcing the law, get my brothers who are equally guilty before you get me and bring me to book.","start":211.119,"stop":234.734,"duration":23.62},{"text":"It was us, when I was a state prosecuting attorney more than a decade ago and it is thus the day with the Federal Trade Commission.","start":234.734,"stop":246.707,"duration":11.97}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"I think at -- if I'm mistaken I thought of the opinion here, almost in every criminal -- is also enough from defense lawyers.","start":246.707,"stop":258.382,"duration":11.68},{"text":"Why don't they bring in bigger picture that this Court (Inaudible) for you gentlemen at the jury.","start":258.382,"stop":268.327,"duration":9.94},{"text":"I think that's a very different thing to say, you shouldn't prosecute A, because he also keeps me from saying that in the domain of commercial regulation, where if it would be true, there's a big “if”.","start":268.327,"stop":283.041,"duration":14.71},{"text":"If A, B and C are competitors, serious competitors and they're all engaged (Inaudible) conscious parallelism, if he can bring all the men and have a trade wise or a proportionately trade-wise order if that can be done certainly it would be a decent administration.","start":283.041,"stop":305.801,"duration":22.76},{"text":"It would be fair to do that and I'm yet -- I'm still trying to see why as you put it before the recess that there aren't such situation such as the (Inaudible) club where you can -- where you can bring them all in.","start":305.801,"stop":319.94,"duration":14.14}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"There had been situations of that character.","start":319.94,"stop":323.728,"duration":3.79},{"text":"Typically, the price fixing situations where the respondents where using a common business practice found to be unlawful and there the Commission --","start":323.728,"stop":334.284,"duration":10.56}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"I'm not talking about conspiracy.","start":334.284,"stop":336.841,"duration":2.56}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"Even there, where the practices were precisely the same, the Commission has issued its two-way count.","start":336.841,"stop":344.432,"duration":7.59},{"text":"Here, the practices are not precisely the same nor would the defenses available to the respondent's be the same.","start":344.432,"stop":357.008,"duration":12.58},{"text":"Where it can and supportive as it is able, the Commission thus move against the principal factors in an industry and situations of this character as indeed it has in this instance.","start":357.008,"stop":370.786,"duration":13.78}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"So you mean in this case, you've given your discretion, the consideration to holding it up but you decide not to hold it up.","start":370.786,"stop":378.243,"duration":7.46}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"The Commission, in each instance, must determine whether or not to proceed in that case at that time or to wait the investigation of other cases and to file several complaints at one time against an industry involving similar practices.","start":378.243,"stop":397.927,"duration":19.68},{"text":"The -- it uses its administrative discretion, its law enforcement discretion, a discretion which from time immoral and our judgment has been used by law enforcement authorities whether they'd be district attorneys or administrative agents.","start":397.927,"stop":416.19,"duration":18.26}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Well you concede that the Court of Appeals could overturn that as it found abuse in your discretion?","start":416.19,"stop":424.889,"duration":8.7}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"No, sir.","start":424.889,"stop":425.971,"duration":1.08},{"text":"I would say that the Court, as Judge Finnegan pointed out in the Niehoff dissent, in the Niehoff case would be interfering in the administrative process and exercising a judgment which belongs peculiarly and is peculiarly within the province of the administrative agency.","start":425.971,"stop":452.078,"duration":26.11}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"You've given -- what you've said that those bulk of your argument is for me at least, a conclusive answer, namely, you deny identity of considerations in the various cases?","start":452.078,"stop":465.179,"duration":13.1}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"I do sir.","start":465.179,"stop":465.386,"duration":0.21}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, that for me is a conclusive answer.","start":465.386,"stop":467.202,"duration":1.82}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"I do, sir.","start":467.202,"stop":468.019,"duration":0.82}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, does that take care of the whole business?","start":468.019,"stop":472.055,"duration":4.04},{"text":"Of course if A, B, and C have different situation?","start":472.055,"stop":474.232,"duration":2.18}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"I think it takes care certainly of this industry, if Your Honor please.","start":474.232,"stop":478.627,"duration":4.39}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, would it have taken care of it if this were a Dallas situation that we discuss this morning?","start":478.627,"stop":486.219,"duration":7.59},{"text":"In that instance, would you say the Court of Appeals could not reach the failure to proceed jointly against all the offenders as the abuse of discretion?","start":486.219,"stop":497.37,"duration":11.15}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"In that instance involving buying groups, the Commission has moved against the (Voice Overlap) --","start":497.37,"stop":502.892,"duration":5.52}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"I know it has but suppose it did not moved against only one of the companies and then you were brought before the Court of Appeals for failure to have moved against all of it.","start":502.892,"stop":518.366,"duration":15.47}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"I think it's possible -- altogether possible that even in this instance, there might have been a defense available to one of those factors that might not have been available to another.","start":518.366,"stop":535.559,"duration":17.19}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, you have to show that at least here.","start":535.559,"stop":538.5,"duration":2.94}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"The matter of defenses is not -- is --","start":538.5,"stop":543.042,"duration":4.54}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"No.","start":543.042,"stop":543.163,"duration":0.12},{"text":"But wouldn't you --","start":543.163,"stop":543.384,"duration":0.22}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"-- not a matter --","start":543.384,"stop":543.75,"duration":0.37}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"-- have to show that that --","start":543.75,"stop":544.603,"duration":0.85}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"-- the government.","start":544.603,"stop":545.29,"duration":0.69}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"-- possibly was the situation to --","start":545.29,"stop":547.452,"duration":2.16}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"The defense is claimed by the respondent.","start":547.452,"stop":550.03,"duration":2.58}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"I know that.","start":550.03,"stop":550.579,"duration":0.55},{"text":"But I say would you not have had to show as the reason for not having proceeded against them all in that group buying situation that there was a difference?","start":550.579,"stop":560.136,"duration":9.56}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"I don't believe that that would have been an issue where the Commission to issue a complaint in one of those instances.","start":560.136,"stop":567.917,"duration":7.78},{"text":"The issue would have been whether or not the statute violates it.","start":567.917,"stop":573.091,"duration":5.17},{"text":"The Commission would have had to have made in its administrative capacity, the determination against how many of those respondents to have or to proceed against.","start":573.091,"stop":584.778,"duration":11.69}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, let me put it this way.","start":584.778,"stop":586.033,"duration":1.25},{"text":"Are you then claiming for the Commission an unreviewable discretion whether to proceed against one or all of a group equally guilty?","start":586.033,"stop":598.18,"duration":12.15}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"I think the Commission can be forced to exercise its administrative discretion as it was in the American Chain and Cable case were Judge Parker in that Circuit said that the Commission should have ruled upon a motion to hold in advance the order during war time and at the request of the War Navy Department.","start":598.18,"stop":621.08,"duration":22.9},{"text":"The Court didn't say that the Commission should have granted the motion.","start":621.08,"stop":625.872,"duration":4.79},{"text":"It said that the Commission should have taken jurisdiction over the motion and ruled on it, exercising its administrative discretion.","start":625.872,"stop":635.05,"duration":9.18},{"text":"I think that necessarily the problem of how the Commission's spends its law enforcement dollar against whom it must proceed is one which it must make in its capacity as a quasi prosecutor if you will in its administrative capacity.","start":635.05,"stop":657.786,"duration":22.74},{"text":"And then, once it proceeds as the statute says it must do, if it finds the probability of law violation.","start":657.786,"stop":670.097,"duration":12.31},{"text":"Once it proceeds, the statute further says that if it finds the facts are that the law has been violated, it shall issue its cease and desist order.","start":670.097,"stop":681.897,"duration":11.8},{"text":"And then, once again, there comes into play after the issuance of the cease and desist order and as in here, the affirmance or review by the Court, there comes into play the Commission's discretion with respect to securing compliance with that order and the two future stages, the Courts of Appeal are brought into the act.","start":681.897,"stop":707.652,"duration":25.75}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Kintner, if I understood Justice Brennan's question.","start":707.652,"stop":711.274,"duration":3.62},{"text":"If I understood or to your reply -- I -- is not answered so far as my understanding of question and answer (Inaudible).","start":711.274,"stop":719.994,"duration":8.72},{"text":"As I understood his question, it was -- assume the Dallas situation, and that I was saying this is -- you've indicated.","start":719.994,"stop":727.468,"duration":7.47},{"text":"Assume the Dallas situation four or five three or six, I don't care which, a multiple number of records, multiple number who violated an act which doesn't call for any cost to counter anything concededly, the difference between those who belong to buyers group and those who do not.","start":727.468,"stop":750.307,"duration":22.84},{"text":"A motion is made and the Commission does only after one.","start":750.307,"stop":755.743,"duration":5.44},{"text":"A motion is made to stay its order until it enters a civil order against the other.","start":755.743,"stop":761.737,"duration":5.99},{"text":"I understand your order and of course if I hear it correctly that if the Commission doesn't pass on that motion, we will consider this for or if it sends it out and puts it on file, you can get mandamus just as you can get mandamus against the I.C.C. or any other administrative agency to exercise its discretion.","start":761.737,"stop":780.716,"duration":18.98}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, sir.","start":780.716,"stop":781.126,"duration":0.41}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"No doubt about that.","start":781.126,"stop":782.354,"duration":1.23},{"text":"But when -- from there, you went on and saying if it does, that it exercise discretion, period.","start":782.354,"stop":789.187,"duration":6.83},{"text":"As I understood Justice Brennan's question, that's why I like to associate myself with it.","start":789.187,"stop":793.197,"duration":4.01},{"text":"Assuming that simple situation uncomplicated by individualization of cost and all of the rest and the Commission exercised its discretion against to stay in favor of one who belongs to a concededly group class, is that not such an -- such an exercise of its discretion as to constitute an abuse correctable by the Court of Appeals?","start":793.197,"stop":819.831,"duration":26.63},{"text":"And your answer is no to that is it?","start":819.831,"stop":821.851,"duration":2.02}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"I think it would be a dereliction of the -- perhaps of the Commission's duty to word the Congress in performing its statutorily assigned duties with respect to enforcement of the law.","start":821.851,"stop":833.554,"duration":11.7}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, I think it (Voice Overlap) --","start":833.554,"stop":834.049,"duration":0.5}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"And I hesitate -- I hesitate as the chief legal officer of an administrative agency to deny the courts ever, their privilege of ruling, that an administrative agency has abused due process.","start":834.049,"stop":854.174,"duration":20.13}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, it does not go that far to be-- to be correctable by the Court of Appeals.","start":854.174,"stop":858.244,"duration":4.07},{"text":"But when you say “dereliction” that's a big word.","start":858.244,"stop":861.003,"duration":2.76}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, sir.","start":861.003,"stop":861.39,"duration":0.39}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"And to say that, the Court of Appeals, under the authority given by the Federal Trade Commission Act, can't correct a dereliction.","start":861.39,"stop":867.577,"duration":6.19},{"text":"That seems to be rather (Inaudible).","start":867.577,"stop":869.081,"duration":1.5}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"I think, that under the -- it's a matter of the assignment of the respective duties to the Commission and to the Courts of Appeal or the handling for the enforcement of the Robinson-Patman and other statutes.","start":869.081,"stop":887.593,"duration":18.51},{"text":"It's a -- a reasonable division of authority of the administrative -- purely administrative on one hand and the courts review on the other hand.","start":887.593,"stop":898.691,"duration":11.1},{"text":"And I believe that the -- your question can only be resolved by an examination of what the Congress has done with respect to division of powers between the administrative agency and the courts.","start":898.691,"stop":917.497,"duration":18.81}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"I'm not at all.","start":917.497,"stop":918.332,"duration":0.84},{"text":"I'm not -- I wasn't out of hand to say that Congress can withhold all judicial review.","start":918.332,"stop":924.155,"duration":5.82},{"text":"It's not at all clear that it couldn't that it's a very different thing when it gives the review its power -- power to modify and something occurs that is deserving to be characterized or you characterize as a dereliction but that is not for me to believe the Court of Appeals.","start":924.155,"stop":941.975,"duration":17.82}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"I think that the Commission had used its discretion to examine in all the facts with respect to an industry, had made findings on which a court might properly say, “You are wrong,” has not -- such evidence that would justify those findings or you're wrong on the law, then comes into play the court's of power.","start":941.975,"stop":970.954,"duration":28.98}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Kitner, may I just -- before we get to the next case.","start":970.954,"stop":974.159,"duration":3.21},{"text":"May I just ask one question?","start":974.159,"stop":975.994,"duration":1.84},{"text":"Is there any question in your -- your mind as to whether the Commission could have withheld the order if it had desires?","start":975.994,"stop":984.6,"duration":8.61},{"text":"Do you recall it that Mr. Frank said that -- that he -- he questioned whether they could because of the lack of equity powers but is there any question in your mind as to whether they could if they wanted to have held this for one year, two years or until -- until it had made certain other determinations?","start":984.6,"stop":1004.555,"duration":19.95}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"None whatsoever, Mr. Chief Justice.","start":1004.555,"stop":1008.73,"duration":4.18}]}]},{"transcriptTitle":"Oral Argument, FTC v. C. E. Niehoff & Co. - January 14, 1958 (110)","transcriptLink":"https://apps.oyez.org/player/#/warren6/oral_argument_audio/15588","transcript":[{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Number 110, Federal Trade Commission versus C.E. Niehoff & Co.","start":0,"stop":22.036,"duration":22.04}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"May it please --","start":22.036,"stop":22.264,"duration":0.23}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"You may proceed --","start":22.264,"stop":22.609,"duration":0.35}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"-- the Court.","start":22.609,"stop":23.097,"duration":0.49}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"-- Mr. Kintner.","start":23.097,"stop":30.254,"duration":7.16}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"The issue -- the underlying principal issue in this case is almost identical nor identical to that in the case previously argued.","start":30.254,"stop":44.318,"duration":14.06}]},{"speakerName":"Tom C. Clark","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Kintner, there's something you said (Inaudible)","start":44.318,"stop":49.668,"duration":5.35}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, sir.","start":49.668,"stop":51.458,"duration":1.79}]},{"speakerName":"Tom C. Clark","textObjs":[{"text":"I'm not familiar with the details.","start":51.458,"stop":54.883,"duration":3.43},{"text":"Does the Commission have the authority in which (Inaudible)","start":54.883,"stop":62.942,"duration":8.06}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"The Commission has no statutory authority, as such, to issue Trade Practice Conference Rules.","start":62.942,"stop":71.923,"duration":8.98},{"text":"It does so in its general administrative capacity.","start":71.923,"stop":78.399,"duration":6.48},{"text":"It holds -- it has established a purely voluntary procedure, whereby upon petition of industry, it will bring the industry together.","start":78.399,"stop":91.245,"duration":12.85},{"text":"There will be a discussion of the applicable law to the practices of that industry and then on its final and only motion, the Commission will issue Trade Practice Rules which are only effective so long as they reflect the actual state of the law.","start":91.245,"stop":110.563,"duration":19.32},{"text":"There is no penalty for the violation of these Trade Practice Rules.","start":110.563,"stop":113.763,"duration":3.2},{"text":"The penalty is the violation of the statute itself.","start":113.763,"stop":117.645,"duration":3.88}]},{"speakerName":"Tom C. Clark","textObjs":[{"text":"Enforce the Company's to -- to join in the Trade Practice Rules?","start":117.645,"stop":124.105,"duration":6.46}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"No, sir.","start":124.105,"stop":124.895,"duration":0.79},{"text":"It is entirely voluntary.","start":124.895,"stop":127.268,"duration":2.37},{"text":"They do not have to sign pledge cards.","start":127.268,"stop":129.426,"duration":2.16},{"text":"Most of them do.","start":129.426,"stop":130.851,"duration":1.43},{"text":"There are Trade Practice Conference Rules for I believe about 180 American industries covering merely the whole panorama of American Industry and yet, we still have our cases.","start":130.851,"stop":142.539,"duration":11.69},{"text":"The rules, as I have said are only so effective as the involuntary statutory law enforcement power of the Commission, is effective in its day to day work in the issuance of complaints and in the holding of hearings.","start":142.539,"stop":160.508,"duration":17.97},{"text":"And finally, the issuance of cease and desist orders and then in securing compliance with those cease and desist orders after they have been passed upon by the Court and approve.","start":160.508,"stop":174.556,"duration":14.05},{"text":"That is the heart of the agency's work and these voluntary procedures are purely are ancillary.","start":174.556,"stop":181.763,"duration":7.21},{"text":"We hope effective and that we think they are in many instances, but only so effective as the Commission's other law enforcement work or the involuntary nature in effect.","start":181.763,"stop":193.679,"duration":11.92}]},{"speakerName":"Tom C. Clark","textObjs":[{"text":"Did the courts raise it before the Commission?","start":193.679,"stop":198.912,"duration":5.23}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, sir, it has in this instance, the -- the respondent requested.","start":198.912,"stop":209.835,"duration":10.92},{"text":"I think it is of interest to point out in its proposed finding which it offered to the hearing examiner from the Commission's -- and I quote, “from the Commission's press release,” I am referring to a proposed finding of the respondent here, a record at page 975, 977.","start":209.835,"stop":242.133,"duration":32.3},{"text":"“From the Commission's press release issued at the time the complaint was filed herein, it is clearly evident that several complaints were filed at the same time, principally directed at certain buying groups,” and then so forth.","start":242.133,"stop":254.968,"duration":12.83},{"text":"It is submitted that before filing this complaint, the Commission should have first examined respondent's quantity discounts as well as those of its competitors.","start":254.968,"stop":263.276,"duration":8.31},{"text":"If the Commission had then been dissatisfied in any respect with any of those discount filings, it should have proposed discounts which it felt were reasonable for the industry in the light of competitive effects and the actual cost savings at various volume levels of sales, held hearings and by rule eventually, have promulgated fair and equitable quantity discount limits applicable to all competitors in the field.","start":263.276,"stop":288.592,"duration":25.32}]},{"speakerName":"William O. Douglas","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, that was something that he wanted to do before they initiate the proceeding.","start":288.592,"stop":295.165,"duration":6.57}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"This was a suggested finding after the case had been tried for many, many months.","start":295.165,"stop":302.584,"duration":7.42}]},{"speakerName":"William O. Douglas","textObjs":[{"text":"But it said that the Commission's failure to follow any procedures vested under before filing this complaint (Voice Overlap) --","start":302.584,"stop":308.686,"duration":6.1}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"It was contended that this was an abuse of the Commission's expression.","start":308.686,"stop":312.714,"duration":4.03}]},{"speakerName":"William O. Douglas","textObjs":[{"text":"We are considering here -- we are considering here the remedy -- the remedy to be acquired after the violation of law has been established.","start":312.714,"stop":319.5,"duration":6.79}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"After -- after there has -- has been an establishment of the violation of the law and after the --","start":319.5,"stop":325.068,"duration":5.57}]},{"speakerName":"William O. Douglas","textObjs":[{"text":"Where did they raise that point before the Commission that the remedy should be deferred?","start":325.068,"stop":333.06,"duration":7.99}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"That was raised, we think, in this particular proposed finding and the Commission rule on it.","start":333.06,"stop":339.643,"duration":6.58},{"text":"I refer you to a language in the Commission's opinion, which you will find that -- at the record, page 1026.","start":339.643,"stop":347.284,"duration":7.64},{"text":"The Commission stated, “Stating that an order requiring the respondent to terminate against unlawful discriminations will destroy the Niehoff business, when its competitors are not likewise enjoined, appellant request that this proceeding be held in advance until the Commission can place all industry members under identical restrictions.","start":347.284,"stop":369.944,"duration":22.66},{"text":"The pricing practices used by the respondent, however, have been found to be in violation of the law since or continuance by the respondent is likewise unlawful.","start":369.944,"stop":379.911,"duration":9.97},{"text":"“The Commission's duty under the applicable statute is to require their termination forthwith that respondents business maybe at adversely affected by the requirement to cease its unlawful conduct, does not counterbalance the President which would beset by the requested action which it followed.","start":379.911,"stop":398.444,"duration":18.53},{"text":"It would mean that Commission orders would be forever pending and unlawful practices rarely if ever corrected.”","start":398.444,"stop":407.002,"duration":8.56},{"text":"On that language, the Commission bottomed its decision not to hold in advance issuance of its cease and desist order in this case.","start":407.002,"stop":419.339,"duration":12.34}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Dealing with the company in the same industry is in the last statement?","start":419.339,"stop":423.07,"duration":3.73}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"The same industry, the Automotive Replacement Parts Industry.","start":423.07,"stop":427.409,"duration":4.34}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"And were they competitors who moved in Niehoff?","start":427.409,"stop":432.893,"duration":5.48}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, sir.","start":432.893,"stop":434.462,"duration":1.57},{"text":"Oh, they were not competitors in their particular lines.","start":434.462,"stop":438.291,"duration":3.83}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Meaning, what, different lines or different --","start":438.291,"stop":440.815,"duration":2.52}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"In this instance, the -- the industry covered the practices or the lines of ignition, testing equipment and hydraulic equipment.","start":440.815,"stop":454.758,"duration":13.94}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"So, it's different in --","start":454.758,"stop":455.718,"duration":0.96}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"The other industry was pistons and springs.","start":455.718,"stop":457.998,"duration":2.28}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Difference in product, not necessarily difference in custody.","start":457.998,"stop":461.742,"duration":3.74}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"Difference in product and in the case at bar, the respondent gave discounts of zero to 17% and sold to at least one buying group.","start":461.742,"stop":480.666,"duration":18.92},{"text":"There was a breakdown of volume discounts in the record in this case in the findings and I believe it is referred to in the Court's opinion below, as to the volume discounts of 10 of the competitors.","start":480.666,"stop":497.542,"duration":16.88},{"text":"Two granted no volume discounts at all, one granted a maximum of 15%, five, 20%, one, 23% and one, 25%.","start":497.542,"stop":509.007,"duration":11.47},{"text":"None of the 10 coincided with the maximum 17% of the respondent here and seven of the 10 had a higher maximum than the respondent here.","start":509.007,"stop":522.251,"duration":13.24},{"text":"There was an analysis of 522 comparative prices.","start":522.251,"stop":527.739,"duration":5.49},{"text":"Among these 10 competitors, 226 were higher than those of the respondent.","start":527.739,"stop":534.158,"duration":6.42},{"text":"152 were lower and 144 were the same.","start":534.158,"stop":544.715,"duration":10.56},{"text":"Numerous complaints were issued in this industry.","start":544.715,"stop":550.089,"duration":5.37},{"text":"I have mentioned that 16 covered the 2 (a) or price discrimination features alone and the buying groups have also been concurrently, preceded against.","start":550.089,"stop":562.949,"duration":12.86},{"text":"There are I believe 24, total of 24 complaints in this industry and I pointed out that the Commission has committed over the nine-year period 25% or more of its price discrimination law enforcement dollar to this one industry.","start":562.949,"stop":586.144,"duration":23.2},{"text":"Certainly, I think some indication of the fact that it had -- it has used its administrative discretion enforcing a law to the fullest within the means that it's disposable.","start":586.144,"stop":609.358,"duration":23.21},{"text":"The court below pointed out that it was unwilling to participate in the economic death of a law violator.","start":609.358,"stop":618.951,"duration":9.59},{"text":"However, the court below may well have ordered the execution of other innocent violators.","start":618.951,"stop":627.724,"duration":8.77},{"text":"I have reference to these independent jobbers who have been forced to join the buying groups as a means of securing more favorable prices from these manufacturers.","start":627.724,"stop":644.173,"duration":16.45},{"text":"Thus, setting in the motion, a ground of illegality, pattern of illegality which is never ending and respondent asked that this Court confirmed into the law, into the administrative process something which would constitute.","start":644.173,"stop":668.422,"duration":24.25},{"text":"I say it advisably, a law enforcement's nightmare were to become a part of any person or the administrative agency.","start":668.422,"stop":692.685,"duration":24.26}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"In what other agency Mr. Kintner, what other agencies would be confronted by a cognate problem of a -- assuming simplified uniform practice that they're assuming, I'm putting to one side the assumption to falsify that fact, to which what other agency?","start":692.685,"stop":719.949,"duration":27.26},{"text":"I'm thinking of the -- the suggestion you made, you'll hear your agencies like do (Inaudible) federal power commission et cetera.","start":719.949,"stop":731.423,"duration":11.47},{"text":"I was wondering whether those agencies almost inherent that one can use of dangerous words and each cases has been individualized.","start":731.423,"stop":743.156,"duration":11.73}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, sir.","start":743.156,"stop":743.521,"duration":0.37},{"text":"And yet, one of the leading cases in this field involved the Federal Communications Commission.","start":743.521,"stop":752.611,"duration":9.09},{"text":"And there, there was a complaint because the Federal Communications Commission had -- unless this is the Pottsville Broadcasting case, had consolidated three cases.","start":752.611,"stop":767.741,"duration":15.13},{"text":"And this Court, speaking through, Mr. Justice Frankfurter that the courts are not charged with general guardianship against all potential mischief in the complicated task of the Government.","start":767.741,"stop":779.472,"duration":11.73},{"text":"Interference by the courts is not conducive to the development of habits of responsibility and administrative agencies.","start":779.472,"stop":787.848,"duration":8.38},{"text":"And then, the Court went on to point out that what is the issue, is not the relationship of the federal courts and to say a relationship define largely by the courts themselves, but to do observance by the courts of the distribution of authority made by Congress as between its power to regulate commerce and the reviewing power which it has conferred upon courts, under Article 3 of the Constitution.","start":787.848,"stop":814.869,"duration":27.02}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"I wrote that when I was young and I still believe it.","start":814.869,"stop":817.342,"duration":2.47}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, we believe that, Your Honor, spoke just as meaningfully in the case of Scripps-Howard Radio versus F.C.C. in 1942 case, when it -- when Your Honor said generally speaking judicial review of administrative orders as limited to determining whether errors of law had been committed, because of historical differences between the administrative bodies and reviewing courts and that between upper and lower courts, a court of review exhaust its power when it lays bare a misconception of law and compels correction.","start":817.342,"stop":855.425,"duration":38.08},{"text":"What Mr. -- what Judge Parker was referring to in the American Chain & Cable case, when he sent back to the administrative agency, the question of whether or not it should hold in advance its order and said, “Without my full -- without intermitting what action, if any, should be taken by the Commission on the motion of petitioners.”","start":855.425,"stop":877.2,"duration":21.78},{"text":"In other words, it was a matter for the discretion of the administrative agency.","start":877.2,"stop":884.314,"duration":7.11},{"text":"It should decide.","start":884.314,"stop":886.37,"duration":2.06}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Well but that -- but I think without intermitting, if one wants to say, it's not reviewable at all, I think one would phrase that the difference in this case, well I think, it's none of our business.","start":886.37,"stop":900.02,"duration":13.65},{"text":"In any event -- in any event, I don't think that the Court should do it.","start":900.02,"stop":903.758,"duration":3.74}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"It's so great -- so great is --","start":903.758,"stop":905.553,"duration":1.79}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"What's the difference -- it's a very different thing if you have -- simply a word dereliction where you shouldn't go back -- enter back to the Commission and say “You consider it those rules are out of hand.”","start":905.553,"stop":916.809,"duration":11.26}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"So great is the --","start":916.809,"stop":916.867,"duration":0.06}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"I'm not saying either of these cases justify that.","start":916.867,"stop":919.706,"duration":2.84}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"So great is the power of the Court under -- of an Article 3 Court under the Constitution that I hesitate to flatly say that this question shall never be subject to review, because it is a part of the function of the courts to make sure that administrative agencies do exercise due process.","start":919.706,"stop":943.694,"duration":23.99},{"text":"But it's even more incumbent upon those agencies if the administration, if the administrative process means anything that they in the first instance and using that great discretion given to them by the Congress, do exercise a full measure of due process, do lean over backwards to a Court, fairness and equality of treatment to all, similarly circumstance.","start":943.694,"stop":970.831,"duration":27.14},{"text":"I believe that and I believe also that the Commission in these instances has done so, has leaned over backwards to treat those similarly situated --","start":970.831,"stop":983.117,"duration":12.29}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Would you --","start":983.117,"stop":983.361,"duration":0.24}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"To clean up the -- the industry.","start":983.361,"stop":985.34,"duration":1.98}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Would you -- would you agree that the Commission must exercise discretion and exercising discretion in power?","start":985.34,"stop":996.362,"duration":11.02}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"I most certainly do, sir, in the same way that a court must do so.","start":996.362,"stop":1004.516,"duration":8.15},{"text":"In other words, justice cannot be weighed out pound by pound like potatoes or sugar.","start":1004.516,"stop":1015.297,"duration":10.78}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"No, but Mr. --","start":1015.297,"stop":1015.764,"duration":0.47}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"Either in the courts or in the administrative agency.","start":1015.764,"stop":1018.576,"duration":2.81}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, Mr. Kintner, in this case, as I understand the -- the opinion of the Commission, the one you referred us to at 1026, the refusal to stay in that order is not on any grounds, as I understand it, that there was a difference which requires the individualization of these cases.","start":1018.576,"stop":1040.207,"duration":21.63},{"text":"But solely, it stated at least that the Commission orders would be forever pending in an unlawful practice merely if it ever corrected.","start":1040.207,"stop":1051.583,"duration":11.38}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, sir.","start":1051.583,"stop":1051.971,"duration":0.39},{"text":"The Commission --","start":1051.971,"stop":1055.215,"duration":3.24}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"So, was that in -- discretion wasn't exercised here on any ground that whatever these practices are under the extent the practice by a competitors of Niehoff --","start":1055.215,"stop":1066.483,"duration":11.27}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"In effect, the Commission --","start":1066.483,"stop":1067.019,"duration":0.54}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"-- that they could not have been reached in the joint proceeding.","start":1067.019,"stop":1069.283,"duration":2.26},{"text":"That was not the ground of determination was it?","start":1069.283,"stop":1072.785,"duration":3.5}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"That is right.","start":1072.785,"stop":1073.443,"duration":0.66},{"text":"The Commission in effect said that it would not exercise its discretion in this instance.","start":1073.443,"stop":1079.793,"duration":6.35},{"text":"In fact, the case had been primarily, tried upon other issues.","start":1079.793,"stop":1086.375,"duration":6.58},{"text":"Respondent attempted two principal defenses, a cost justification defense and a defense that its practices were made in good faith -- in good faith to meet competition.","start":1086.375,"stop":1099.957,"duration":13.58}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, now --","start":1099.957,"stop":1100.399,"duration":0.44}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"It did (Voice Overlap) --","start":1100.399,"stop":1101.741,"duration":1.34}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Are you suggesting that the application for a joint inquiry was not made when this proceeding started, but rather after it has been resolved against Niehoff, then Niehoff asked for a stay of the effectiveness of the cease and desist order, is that it?","start":1101.741,"stop":1119.12,"duration":17.38}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"The -- no, sir.","start":1119.12,"stop":1120.925,"duration":1.81},{"text":"Not -- not entirely.","start":1120.925,"stop":1122.989,"duration":2.06},{"text":"While the case primarily was tried with respect to the question of these two defenses and then of course, collaterally with respect to the -- and finally, with respect to the question of injury to competition, there was evidence submitted by the hearing examiner in the record, with respect to the pricing practices of some of respondent's competitors.","start":1122.989,"stop":1151.989,"duration":29}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, at what point was the application made, to treat them all at the same time?","start":1151.989,"stop":1158.085,"duration":6.1},{"text":"At what point in this proceeding?","start":1158.085,"stop":1161.182,"duration":3.1}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"The -- the application was made to the hearing examiner, in effect, in proposed findings and to the Commission during oral argument of this matter on the merits before the Commission and the Commission --","start":1161.182,"stop":1177.563,"duration":16.38}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"That is on the merit whether -- whether or not it was a violation or on the merits to the form of order?","start":1177.563,"stop":1182.654,"duration":5.09}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"All the merits with respect to whether an order would be proper in this instance and were it proper with respect to whether or not it should be held in advance until all similarly situated competitors were brought to book.","start":1182.654,"stop":1199.292,"duration":16.64}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, and -- and the Commission then finally turned their determination, not on any ground of dissimilarity among competitors and between the competitors and the Niehoff, but solely for the ground stated here, is that it?","start":1199.292,"stop":1214.807,"duration":15.52}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"That is right.","start":1214.807,"stop":1218.065,"duration":3.26}]},{"speakerName":"Tom C. Clark","textObjs":[{"text":"Of course, some of its (Inaudible)","start":1218.065,"stop":1229.462,"duration":11.4}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, sir.","start":1229.462,"stop":1229.938,"duration":0.48},{"text":"The chronology in this case indicates that the Commission's case was tried in 11 months.","start":1229.938,"stop":1236.436,"duration":6.5},{"text":"The respondent's case defense took two and half years.","start":1236.436,"stop":1240.806,"duration":4.37},{"text":"The matter was in the administrative decisional process.","start":1240.806,"stop":1244.156,"duration":3.35},{"text":"That is the briefing before the hearing examiner and the briefing before the Commission for one year and it has been before the courts for two and a half years.","start":1244.156,"stop":1252.472,"duration":8.32},{"text":"Now again, this is not a typical case because it involved a -- a practice that has -- has been pointed was common at least superficially to certain parts of the industry, if not, a substantial part of the industry.","start":1252.472,"stop":1268.485,"duration":16.01},{"text":"It involved a new industry which had not been previously examined by the Commission.","start":1268.485,"stop":1275.427,"duration":6.94},{"text":"And necessarily, the -- the first impression cases were long cases and the case was brought with respect to a statute which has provide certain defenses, which respondents are entitled to avail themselves of and not necessarily as time consuming.","start":1275.427,"stop":1296.592,"duration":21.17}]},{"speakerName":"UNKNOWN","textObjs":[{"text":"Is this the whole record?","start":1296.592,"stop":1301.672,"duration":5.08}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"Now this, I believe, is the whole record.","start":1301.672,"stop":1306.174,"duration":4.5}]},{"speakerName":"UNKNOWN","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible)","start":1306.174,"stop":1308.537,"duration":2.36}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"There were many delays while accountants examined the cost accounting.","start":1308.537,"stop":1317.327,"duration":8.79},{"text":"Cost justification is a very difficult and technical problem.","start":1317.327,"stop":1323.937,"duration":6.61},{"text":"And the respondents were given every reasonable opportunity to adduce any evidence which might be favorable to their cause.","start":1323.937,"stop":1335.787,"duration":11.85},{"text":"Perhaps, the Commission's examiner was too lenient in that regard, but I for one would rather see more time elapsed and the ends of justice better served, if that does become necessary.","start":1335.787,"stop":1349.247,"duration":13.46},{"text":"I would like to reserve the remaining portion of my time for rebuttal.","start":1349.247,"stop":1353.646,"duration":4.4}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes.","start":1353.646,"stop":1360.92,"duration":7.27},{"text":"Mr. Sprowl.","start":1360.92,"stop":1362.298,"duration":1.38}]},{"speakerName":"Charles R. Sprowl","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Chief Justice, Justices of the Supreme Court, Mr. Kintner.","start":1362.298,"stop":1369.61,"duration":7.31},{"text":"I would first like to point out to the Court the specific language of the statute, which gives to the Federal Trade Commission the power to place for the time within which any order it entered goes into effect.","start":1369.61,"stop":1386.436,"duration":16.83},{"text":"It appears in -- in the Section 11 at page 4 of the Commission's brief, stating the power of the Commission towards the end of the second paragraph that it accurately finds a violation that shall issue in cause to be served on such portion, an order referring such person to cease and desist from such violations and then taking up at the end in the manner and within the time fixed by said order.","start":1386.436,"stop":1416.727,"duration":30.29},{"text":"So the Commission does have the power to fix the time within which cease and desist order will become effective.","start":1416.727,"stop":1424.863,"duration":8.14},{"text":"And by the same token, the Court of Appeals under the Eastman Kodak case would have a like power since the Commission is in turn vested with that power.","start":1424.863,"stop":1436.919,"duration":12.06},{"text":"In this particular case, Niehoff Company manufactured primarily a line of ignition parts, replacement parts for automobiles.","start":1436.919,"stop":1446.826,"duration":9.91},{"text":"It has 19 competitors, three of whom are the big three in the automotive industry, Ford, General Motors and Chrysler and 16 other competitors of the aftermarket variety like Niehoff.","start":1446.826,"stop":1463.628,"duration":16.8},{"text":"Proof was made of the identity of all of those competitors at a hearing held May 15, 1952.","start":1463.628,"stop":1473.833,"duration":10.21}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Now, what stage of the proceeding?","start":1473.833,"stop":1475.517,"duration":1.68}]},{"speakerName":"Charles R. Sprowl","textObjs":[{"text":"That was at the very outset of the respondent's case.","start":1475.517,"stop":1480.226,"duration":4.71},{"text":"Immediately thereafter, that was the beginning of our defense that we had much competition in this field that we were perhaps meeting there equally low prices in good faith, but that also, we would be seriously hurt if we were placed under an injunction while our competitors were free of a similar restraint.","start":1480.226,"stop":1503.662,"duration":23.44},{"text":"After that, the Commission did see fit to file complaints against two of our competitors, but it is not seen fit to act as to any other competitors in the meantime.","start":1503.662,"stop":1515.378,"duration":11.72},{"text":"I think the record makes it clear what really happened here.","start":1515.378,"stop":1518.769,"duration":3.39},{"text":"The Commission started it out in the first instance to bring test cases against buying groups in the automotive industry.","start":1518.769,"stop":1528.196,"duration":9.43},{"text":"The job for buying groups, it was bond together to build up volume and qualify for a higher quantity discounts.","start":1528.196,"stop":1535.492,"duration":7.3},{"text":"It's -- at the time the complaint was issued against the Niehoff Company, it primarily issued its complaint against members of a buying group called Cotton States.","start":1535.492,"stop":1546.296,"duration":10.8},{"text":"And its publicity release show that the time that those complaints were issued including one against the Niehoff Company, it was clear that they then issued two or three complaints against, I believe, Niehoff and a company named Edelmann in an unrelated line of automotive replacement parts and perhaps one other to round out the picture.","start":1546.296,"stop":1569.061,"duration":22.76},{"text":"Obviously, the manufacturers at that point were the caboose on this train of enforcement.","start":1569.061,"stop":1574.988,"duration":5.93},{"text":"At a little later in this proceeding, about the same time this evidence was being put in as to the nature of Niehoff's competition, we made proof of the fact that while the Commission had in the meantime proceeded vigorously against Niehoff, it started to show that it had done nothing in the Cotton States matter.","start":1574.988,"stop":1596.352,"duration":21.36},{"text":"That stirred up the tempest and they shortly started to turn their wheels in Cotton States, but the point is that the reason the whole proceeding in this ignition field is so poorly conceived by the Commission is what they started out to do, was to police group buying and they ended up merely trying to get the Niehoff Company which sells ignition parts under a cease and desist order.","start":1596.352,"stop":1622.236,"duration":25.88},{"text":"At every stage of this proceeding, we not only made proof of our competition of the fact that they used substantially similar discounts.","start":1622.236,"stop":1630.686,"duration":8.45},{"text":"We gave them the copies of their contracts that were being used.","start":1630.686,"stop":1634.307,"duration":3.62},{"text":"We put them in evidence.","start":1634.307,"stop":1636.486,"duration":2.18},{"text":"We gave them dates, names and places.","start":1636.486,"stop":1638.884,"duration":2.4},{"text":"We may prove to the fact that if we were under such an injunction, while our competitors were not similarly enjoined in this highly competitive field, we would be put out of business by the order and they all fell on deaf ears.","start":1638.884,"stop":1653.954,"duration":15.07},{"text":"When we got down to the conclusion of the evidence and I wish to say that I don't recall the reasons for the delay in this case why did Mr. Kintner explained this.","start":1653.954,"stop":1666.588,"duration":12.63},{"text":"I recall one substantial delay because the Commission made it clear that they've run out money at that point for the current year for travelling and what we put over the hearings for several months until their next physical budget came into effect which we did.","start":1666.588,"stop":1682.676,"duration":16.09},{"text":"The -- there was extensive time taken in this matter in cross-examination, in our case by the Commission attorneys which explained some part of the delay and the printed book is not the complete record of the Commission in bringing this case up.","start":1682.676,"stop":1697.668,"duration":14.99},{"text":"It does not see fit to bring up the exhibits, which were filed as exhibits unprinted in the court below.","start":1697.668,"stop":1707.444,"duration":9.78},{"text":"When we came before the -- to the point where we have to make request for findings of fact of the trial examiner, we made two requests.","start":1707.444,"stop":1717.649,"duration":10.2},{"text":"One was really, merely a conclusion of fact that the Commission's action was an abusive discretion.","start":1717.649,"stop":1724.384,"duration":6.74},{"text":"I believe that's our last request of finding 75.","start":1724.384,"stop":1729.634,"duration":5.25},{"text":"And then, we have 141, which detailed the fact that Niehoff -- the evidence would show that Niehoff would be put out of business.","start":1729.634,"stop":1739.226,"duration":9.59},{"text":"It will replace under this order while its competition was not similarly treated.","start":1739.226,"stop":1745.437,"duration":6.21},{"text":"As to one of those, the hearing examiner found it was beyond his jurisdiction and as to other he refused to make a finding.","start":1745.437,"stop":1752.012,"duration":6.58},{"text":"And then, before the Federal Trade Commission as such on appeal from the hearing examiner's decision and a brief which we filed or dated November 15th, 1954.","start":1752.012,"stop":1764.988,"duration":12.98},{"text":"We devoted an extensive portion of that brief to this particular request, all the matter in advance or to further order or do something while they took action against our competition and that Section set forth the evidence which showed that Niehoff would be financially ruined by the order if its competition were free of the order in the meantime and that is the portion of our brief and the argument that related to an oral argument which prompted the comment, which appears in the opinion of the Commission.","start":1764.988,"stop":1798.842,"duration":33.85}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Is the -- Mr. Sprowl, may I ask this?","start":1798.842,"stop":1801.534,"duration":2.69},{"text":"It's the record of a thousand pages, what portion of that record (Inaudible) opinion?","start":1801.534,"stop":1811.134,"duration":9.6},{"text":"What portion of that record to your point of view is relevant to what you conceive to be the issue before this Court?","start":1811.134,"stop":1816.985,"duration":5.85}]},{"speakerName":"Charles R. Sprowl","textObjs":[{"text":"On the issue before this Court, I would -- I would doubt that more than 50 or 100 pages.","start":1816.985,"stop":1825.655,"duration":8.67}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"If you've got a record of a thousand.","start":1825.655,"stop":1827.689,"duration":2.03}]},{"speakerName":"Charles R. Sprowl","textObjs":[{"text":"That's because it was printed out in full in the court below.","start":1827.689,"stop":1831.398,"duration":3.71}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Oh, this is just --","start":1831.398,"stop":1833.356,"duration":1.96}]},{"speakerName":"Charles R. Sprowl","textObjs":[{"text":"That's right.","start":1833.356,"stop":1833.638,"duration":0.28}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Treatment (Inaudible)","start":1833.638,"stop":1834.858,"duration":1.22}]},{"speakerName":"Charles R. Sprowl","textObjs":[{"text":"I think it's just a -- that was the record as we printed it for the Court of Appeals in the Seventh Circuit.","start":1834.858,"stop":1841.306,"duration":6.45},{"text":"And then, they -- then they added to it the proceedings in the Court of Appeals and put a new cover on it, and that -- and that was filed at the time the petition for certiorari was --","start":1841.306,"stop":1849.789,"duration":8.48}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"I thought -- I thought it wasn't visible.","start":1849.789,"stop":1851.691,"duration":1.9},{"text":"A thousand page is relevant (Voice Overlap) --","start":1851.691,"stop":1853.479,"duration":1.79}]},{"speakerName":"Charles R. Sprowl","textObjs":[{"text":"You're -- you're absolutely right.","start":1853.479,"stop":1855.803,"duration":2.32}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"I take that the brief --","start":1855.803,"stop":1855.989,"duration":0.19}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Sprowl, when -- when the examiner stated that this was beyond his jurisdiction, was he speaking only beyond the scope of his authority as an examiner or is he speaking about the jurisdiction of the Commission?","start":1855.989,"stop":1873.172,"duration":17.18}]},{"speakerName":"Charles R. Sprowl","textObjs":[{"text":"I think he was speaking of his own jurisdiction.","start":1873.172,"stop":1875.607,"duration":2.43},{"text":"Here, we were asking the hearing examiner to find that the Commission, the Federal Trade Commission has been guilty of an abuse of discretion.","start":1875.607,"stop":1884.103,"duration":8.5},{"text":"And perhaps through sensibility of his own part, he preferred not to make such a finding.","start":1884.103,"stop":1892.768,"duration":8.66},{"text":"I don't really know what was in his mind but I think he meant beyond his own personal jurisdiction, but we did make the point at every stage of this proceeding.","start":1892.768,"stop":1902.074,"duration":9.31},{"text":"And we -- when we took the matter before the United States Court of Appeal, that was one of our assignments of error and it was on that basis that the Court acted.","start":1902.074,"stop":1913.573,"duration":11.5},{"text":"Now, there's no --","start":1913.573,"stop":1913.709,"duration":0.14}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Is this question argued orally before the Commission?","start":1913.709,"stop":1916.932,"duration":3.22}]},{"speakerName":"Charles R. Sprowl","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes.","start":1916.932,"stop":1917.785,"duration":0.85},{"text":"Yes, it was and I was asked questions concerning that way.","start":1917.785,"stop":1920.787,"duration":3}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Any other grounds which Mr. Kintner has based the propriety of the Commission's action argued their?","start":1920.787,"stop":1929.911,"duration":9.12}]},{"speakerName":"Charles R. Sprowl","textObjs":[{"text":"I only argued it to the -- I think, I'm the only that argued it, as I recall it and I merely made a statement of fact but I probably would like -- I repeated the evidence as it showed that Niehoff would be put out of business.","start":1929.911,"stop":1942.516,"duration":12.61},{"text":"I don't --","start":1942.516,"stop":1942.606,"duration":0.09}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"What I'm trying to get at was it suggested at all that there were any practical reasons why competitors also, if so, were so guilty of this practice, could not have enjoined?","start":1942.606,"stop":1952.918,"duration":10.31}]},{"speakerName":"Charles R. Sprowl","textObjs":[{"text":"None -- none whatsoever.","start":1952.918,"stop":1954.199,"duration":1.28}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"It was not suggested at any time?","start":1954.199,"stop":1955.085,"duration":0.89}]},{"speakerName":"Charles R. Sprowl","textObjs":[{"text":"Never suggested, no, except for what might appear in the opinion of the Commission.","start":1955.085,"stop":1959.526,"duration":4.44},{"text":"That's the only --","start":1959.526,"stop":1960.286,"duration":0.76}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, I don't find anything in the opinion of the Commission if I --","start":1960.286,"stop":1963.063,"duration":2.78}]},{"speakerName":"Charles R. Sprowl","textObjs":[{"text":"It's just what you read, Your Honor.","start":1963.063,"stop":1964.373,"duration":1.31}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"-- one paragraph.","start":1964.373,"stop":1966.442,"duration":2.07}]},{"speakerName":"Charles R. Sprowl","textObjs":[{"text":"That's all.","start":1966.442,"stop":1966.585,"duration":0.14}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Sprowl, am I right to put -- I gather from Mr. Kintner's argument the diversion of this case is that the Commission was entitled to have reasonable grounds if there's an expert party to say that there were such differences among the competitors (Inaudible) but you couldn't that it was entitled to say that they couldn't all be brought into a single proceeding.That's the burden of the (Inaudible).","start":1966.585,"stop":2001.673,"duration":35.09}]},{"speakerName":"Charles R. Sprowl","textObjs":[{"text":"I gather that's what he said, Your Honor.","start":2001.673,"stop":2003.52,"duration":1.85}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, that's what he said.","start":2003.52,"stop":2004.46,"duration":0.94},{"text":"Now, if you will address yourself to that in particular, would you -- because if it's true, you could hardly deny it, I suppose Mr. Sprowl, that the Commission, an agency must be given discretion of the Commission (Inaudible) and say we can't bring them all in one proceeding, have a counsel table over 20 lawyers and different witnesses (Inaudible) that it must be successive -- progressive.","start":2004.46,"stop":2035.211,"duration":30.75}]},{"speakerName":"Charles R. Sprowl","textObjs":[{"text":"It might well be and they have done it that way in the past.","start":2035.211,"stop":2038.178,"duration":2.97},{"text":"My point is simply this.","start":2038.178,"stop":2039.595,"duration":1.42},{"text":"Have they seen fit at the time they filed a complaint against Niehoff to understood the Automotive and Ignition Parts Replacement Industry or have they -- when we made the proof of the nature of it or just a year or so later.","start":2039.595,"stop":2052.897,"duration":13.3},{"text":"It seemed fit through then filed a complaint separately if you wish against these 16 or 17 competitors.","start":2052.897,"stop":2061.704,"duration":8.81},{"text":"We would not be in this position where one company to which the Niehoff Company is out of step and everyone else is free to use this volume discount methods of sale.","start":2061.704,"stop":2071.954,"duration":10.25}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Between the filing of the petitioner's complaint and the order in this case, how much time is left?","start":2071.954,"stop":2081.152,"duration":9.2}]},{"speakerName":"Charles R. Sprowl","textObjs":[{"text":"The order of the Commission?","start":2081.152,"stop":2082.591,"duration":1.44}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes.","start":2082.591,"stop":2083.168,"duration":0.58}]},{"speakerName":"Charles R. Sprowl","textObjs":[{"text":"I believe the Commission's order was entered late in 50 -- middle of 1954.","start":2083.168,"stop":2087.32,"duration":4.15},{"text":"So, that was over four years.","start":2087.32,"stop":2089.895,"duration":2.57}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"So, that --","start":2089.895,"stop":2090.609,"duration":0.71}]},{"speakerName":"Charles R. Sprowl","textObjs":[{"text":"About four years.","start":2090.609,"stop":2090.658,"duration":0.05}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"-- do I gather -- do I gather that you wouldn't -- you wouldn't be here if it actually filed a complaint against the competitors, each taking successively four years (Inaudible)","start":2090.658,"stop":2099.892,"duration":9.23}]},{"speakerName":"Charles R. Sprowl","textObjs":[{"text":"I'm satisfied we wouldn't be here for this reason and I have an experience with the Commission on a similar matter not too many years ago.","start":2099.892,"stop":2107.368,"duration":7.48},{"text":"It brought a multiple complaint against a group called the Fashion Originators' Guild that they had to do with this handling and keeping of piracy out of dressmaking in New York.","start":2107.368,"stop":2120.03,"duration":12.66},{"text":"They included in that many retail stores.","start":2120.03,"stop":2123.699,"duration":3.67},{"text":"It was adjudicated to be an improper practice, the principles of manufacturers decided to appeal at the Second Circuit.","start":2123.699,"stop":2132.243,"duration":8.54},{"text":"Such door is out in our way, Marshall Field and Company in Chicago and a company.","start":2132.243,"stop":2138.246,"duration":6},{"text":"I know a store in Detroit.","start":2138.246,"stop":2139.534,"duration":1.29},{"text":"It was then faced with a proposition.","start":2139.534,"stop":2141.364,"duration":1.83},{"text":"If we don't appeal, the order will be final as to us and it might be reversed as to the manufacturers.","start":2141.364,"stop":2147.923,"duration":6.56},{"text":"So, we filed the skeleton appeal.","start":2147.923,"stop":2150.669,"duration":2.75},{"text":"I recall one from Marshall Field in the Seventh Circuit and one for Hudson in Detroit in the Sixth Circuit and stipulated over the Commission that we would abide the result of the decision of the Second Circuit and it worked beautifully.","start":2150.669,"stop":2162.479,"duration":11.81},{"text":"And there is no reason why in this proceeding against the 16 people at the similar complaints being filed.","start":2162.479,"stop":2169.401,"duration":6.92},{"text":"We would have been more than happy to stipulate it to abide the result anyone of those cases on the fundamental proposition of the legality of quantity discounts of the nature that are used in the industry and I think it would have greatly simplify it.","start":2169.401,"stop":2184.905,"duration":15.5},{"text":"That was the very thing we have urged.","start":2184.905,"stop":2186.655,"duration":1.75},{"text":"We were urging and talking about throughout this proceeding, because certainly the Niehoff Company is -- is not anxious to spend its money and pioneer in the law.","start":2186.655,"stop":2197.234,"duration":10.58},{"text":"It only finds itself at an impossible position and that it's compelled to do what it is now trying to do to keep itself from being put out of business.","start":2197.234,"stop":2206.095,"duration":8.86}]},{"speakerName":"Tom C. Clark","textObjs":[{"text":"When did you first ask the Commission itself (Inaudible)","start":2206.095,"stop":2210.576,"duration":4.48}]},{"speakerName":"Charles R. Sprowl","textObjs":[{"text":"The first time we asked the Commission, and I'm speaking of the members of the Commission, was at the time we filed our brief with the Commission, which was our -- actually, our first appearance before them and the day to that brief is November 15, 1954 and I don't recall when the arguments were that followed their filling of that brief that it was within 30 or 60 days thereafter that it was repeated in oral argument.","start":2210.576,"stop":2237.071,"duration":26.49}]},{"speakerName":"Tom C. Clark","textObjs":[{"text":"He's been saying about 4 years.","start":2237.071,"stop":2238.69,"duration":1.62}]},{"speakerName":"Charles R. Sprowl","textObjs":[{"text":"About 4 years.","start":2238.69,"stop":2241.033,"duration":2.34},{"text":"But we had in the meantime made it known to the hearing examiner and to the counsel supporting the complaint to our Federal Trade Commission attorney in the course of the hearing.","start":2241.033,"stop":2250.036,"duration":9}]},{"speakerName":"Tom C. Clark","textObjs":[{"text":"I understand you to say that the examiner is indicating (Inaudible)","start":2250.036,"stop":2257.044,"duration":7.01}]},{"speakerName":"Charles R. Sprowl","textObjs":[{"text":"When we asked for a finding that the Commission was guilty of an abuse of discretion in bringing the proceeding, he refused to make the finding and with probably some propriety.","start":2257.044,"stop":2269.776,"duration":12.73},{"text":"He felt it was beyond his jurisdiction to make such a finding.","start":2269.776,"stop":2273.443,"duration":3.67},{"text":"However, he admitted the evidence in the record into the -- he admitted into the record the evidence which we offered, which showed that Niehoff would be put out of business if it were placed under this restraint while its competitors were not similarly enjoined.","start":2273.443,"stop":2290.916,"duration":17.47}]},{"speakerName":"Tom C. Clark","textObjs":[{"text":"You filed -- I'm asking you this for information.","start":2290.916,"stop":2294.745,"duration":3.83},{"text":"You filed a petition before the Commission itself, calling all their attention and saying exactly (Inaudible)","start":2294.745,"stop":2316.773,"duration":22.03}]},{"speakerName":"Charles R. Sprowl","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, the methods in which the Commission operates are a little mysterious to me and I think properly so they shouldn't tell the source of the basis of the people who are asked to give them information which might lead to complaint that I assume many of them are secret, but we did nothing other than make the proof in this record and then argue it orally to the Commission.","start":2316.773,"stop":2335.127,"duration":18.35},{"text":"We did not write any separate letter or separate complaint to the Commission or file any separate motion.","start":2335.127,"stop":2345.156,"duration":10.03}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, I gather your -- those brief in oral argument, preceded the determination that you were guilty of the violation.","start":2345.156,"stop":2351.472,"duration":6.32}]},{"speakerName":"Charles R. Sprowl","textObjs":[{"text":"Absolutely.","start":2351.472,"stop":2352.632,"duration":1.16}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"So that it was -- the Commission has the opportunity, do I get it, before handing down a finding at all of violation to have proceeded with these other complaints to the same point as yours.","start":2352.632,"stop":2366.39,"duration":13.76}]},{"speakerName":"Charles R. Sprowl","textObjs":[{"text":"That is correct.","start":2366.39,"stop":2367.755,"duration":1.37},{"text":"That is correct and that's all we were asking the Commission to do.","start":2367.755,"stop":2371.272,"duration":3.52}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Sprowl, I -- in the -- in the last case, I understood Mr. Kintner to say that the Commission was already spending 25% of its promulgation in enforcing in this particular field, you folks are again (Inaudible) percentage and I just wonder if -- if that fact bears on the least submissive -- the Commission not undertaking to bring suits against everyone in this -- in this field because you said before you have helped the Commission out in their money gram, how can he come and continue it [Laughs] in a few months.","start":2371.272,"stop":2418.469,"duration":47.2},{"text":"I wonder if a few industries couldn't tie them up in that matter until they couldn't -- couldn't possibly proceed.","start":2418.469,"stop":2425.669,"duration":7.2}]},{"speakerName":"Charles R. Sprowl","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, I can't believe it would be so here, because my whole thesis in this case has been that never before, until this case and the one or two cases in the automotive industry somewhere until it were filed were the quantity discounts as such attacked.","start":2425.669,"stop":2444.228,"duration":18.56},{"text":"As this court stated in the Bruce's Juices cases, it would be a far cry to just say that all quantity discounts were just illegal per se and they -- they haven't been determined to be illegal.","start":2444.228,"stop":2456.343,"duration":12.11},{"text":"It was in a sense a -- a landmark case.","start":2456.343,"stop":2459.9,"duration":3.56},{"text":"Now, I say that the Commission, when they are out to attack a brand new, for the first time an established method of pricing, they shouldn't go around the barn and first start out in a humbling way against some group of buyers and decide that's maybe more than they want to buzz with at the moment and then proceed against the -- one of the manufacturers without making some more critical study of the -- of the industry.","start":2459.9,"stop":2488.63,"duration":28.73},{"text":"And it was a prior to us that they hadn't made it, so that's why we made the proof of the fact that this wasn't a big industry.","start":2488.63,"stop":2494.052,"duration":5.42},{"text":"There are only 18 competitors, 16 of which are the small ones and the ones that we're interested in.","start":2494.052,"stop":2501.292,"duration":7.24},{"text":"It isn't a big job for you to file 16 complaints.","start":2501.292,"stop":2504.116,"duration":2.82},{"text":"It's just a matter of merely grabbing what you have against us and putting a different name on it because the issue is the same.","start":2504.116,"stop":2510.704,"duration":6.59},{"text":"Now, as to the question of the -- of the further defenses, I -- I take issue with Mr. Kintner on that.","start":2510.704,"stop":2517.004,"duration":6.3},{"text":"Admittedly, every respondent has the defense of after -- in a case involving whether or not he's guilty of illegal pricing of showing that he either did it in good faith and made an unequally low price with a competitor or the cost justification offense.","start":2517.004,"stop":2534.787,"duration":17.78},{"text":"Your Honors pointed out in the Ruberoid case even after they issue a cease and desist order.","start":2534.787,"stop":2539.858,"duration":5.07},{"text":"Those two defenses are inherent in the order whether it's -- well, to have those exceptions or not.","start":2539.858,"stop":2545.696,"duration":5.84},{"text":"So actually, once you get to the point of a cease and desist order -- to get to a point of a cease and desist order, really, all you need is to establish that the general pricing system they're using is illegal, that they may have defenses as -- as to certain sales within their surprising policy because at one point they met the equally low price of a competitor or that some part maybe or is or might in the future be cost justified.","start":2545.696,"stop":2571.852,"duration":26.16},{"text":"Those exceptions are inherent in the cease and desist order as Your Honors pointed out properly in the Ruberoid case.","start":2571.852,"stop":2578.497,"duration":6.64},{"text":"So it wasn't.","start":2578.497,"stop":2579.433,"duration":0.94},{"text":"It -- it could have been once you're over the hurry that this type of -- of discount is an illegal pricing method under the Federal Trade Commission under Section 2.","start":2579.433,"stop":2590.458,"duration":11.03},{"text":"It isn't a serious problem.","start":2590.458,"stop":2592.005,"duration":1.55},{"text":"That's the big issue in the case and I -- I just can't believe that it would take all of the time and effort that Mr. Kintner would indicate or in an ordinary law of this you think nothing of making 18 suits instead of one and -- and carrying them along together, it -- as to where the portion of their budget goes in the automotive industry.","start":2592.005,"stop":2614.133,"duration":22.13},{"text":"I think Mr. Kintner is referring not to the ignition field of the automotive replacement parts industry which Niehoff was in but perhaps the entire automotive industry which is so vast, I couldn't begin to describe its limits.","start":2614.133,"stop":2628.437,"duration":14.3}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Sprowl, your interest -- in stating your name (Inaudible) I think that's what you call it.","start":2628.437,"stop":2635.153,"duration":6.72},{"text":"I don't think the Court could respond and subscribe or rather underwrite it could subscribe to your thesis which I underwrite it.","start":2635.153,"stop":2645.021,"duration":9.87},{"text":"If I understood you, you said that the Commission should have had a general investigation and form itself as it were regarding all the particularities (Inaudible) that you have this interest and it has done in other (Voice Overlap) --","start":2645.021,"stop":2659.477,"duration":14.46}]},{"speakerName":"Charles R. Sprowl","textObjs":[{"text":"That's right.","start":2659.477,"stop":2659.856,"duration":0.38}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible)","start":2659.856,"stop":2661.234,"duration":1.38}]},{"speakerName":"Charles R. Sprowl","textObjs":[{"text":"The candy industry?","start":2661.234,"stop":2662.555,"duration":1.32}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, but surely, we can't possibly remotely suggest there to do that.","start":2662.555,"stop":2666.976,"duration":4.42}]},{"speakerName":"Charles R. Sprowl","textObjs":[{"text":"No, but when the respondent himself suggest it and makes it clear that to do what they are doing will put the respondent out of business.","start":2666.976,"stop":2677.627,"duration":10.65},{"text":"It was entered -- it amounts to an abuse of the Commission's discretion and failing to take some other action against its competitors and I think it is abuse and abuse of the Commission's discretion failed to act and there is no question that the Court of Appeals has the power to correct an abuse of -- of discretion by the Commission.","start":2677.627,"stop":2696.63,"duration":19}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"May I ask you?","start":2696.63,"stop":2699.606,"duration":2.98},{"text":"I have no doubt if you say it correctly.","start":2699.606,"stop":2701.778,"duration":2.17},{"text":"You would declare (Inaudible) and I'm thinking about the serious problems that they can (Inaudible), do you think (Inaudible) that time they're actually one place to another then said --","start":2701.778,"stop":2722.204,"duration":20.43}]},{"speakerName":"Charles R. Sprowl","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, I -- I don't --","start":2722.204,"stop":2722.934,"duration":0.73}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"-- in that case.","start":2722.934,"stop":2723.096,"duration":0.16}]},{"speakerName":"Charles R. Sprowl","textObjs":[{"text":"-- alter any question about it.","start":2723.096,"stop":2725.03,"duration":1.93},{"text":"They would want to make their defenses, but my point is that have they -- have the Commission acted with any reasonable dispatch, even insofar as 1954 after we not only made the proof with the competitors were in the nature of their pricing with the decision that they had in the Niehoff case that they held in advance a year or two or three which would have been long passed.","start":2725.03,"stop":2745.477,"duration":20.45},{"text":"Now, they could have had complaints and proceeded to a point where there wouldn't have been any problem, but they just sought it not to act.","start":2745.477,"stop":2751.864,"duration":6.39}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Do you think it's really practical or can be practiced to which (Inaudible)","start":2751.864,"stop":2758.713,"duration":6.85}]},{"speakerName":"Charles R. Sprowl","textObjs":[{"text":"I do (Inaudible)","start":2758.713,"stop":2759.293,"duration":0.58}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Interminable delays that they should bring in all of the (Voice Overlap) --","start":2759.293,"stop":2764.045,"duration":4.75}]},{"speakerName":"Charles R. Sprowl","textObjs":[{"text":"I think where the industry is no greater than these 16 or 18 that were concerned with here.","start":2764.045,"stop":2772.393,"duration":8.35},{"text":"There -- there -- the evidence shows that they are not in violation.","start":2772.393,"stop":2776.107,"duration":3.71},{"text":"The point is that they are the dominant factors and these other people have to place their merchandise under it.","start":2776.107,"stop":2782.165,"duration":6.06},{"text":"It's the -- it's the 15 little ones or 16 little ones that have the discount that (Inaudible) and Ford do not.","start":2782.165,"stop":2791.92,"duration":9.76},{"text":"They're just merely in there as competitors.","start":2791.92,"stop":2795.48,"duration":3.56}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"You argued that when there was a small number (Inaudible) one party raises the objection that other than -- all of it that's engaged in this activity that the Commission should have discretion before.","start":2795.48,"stop":2812.538,"duration":17.06},{"text":"Now, if it has a discretion (Inaudible) bring all of them in so that whoever (Inaudible)","start":2812.538,"stop":2822.545,"duration":10.01}]},{"speakerName":"Charles R. Sprowl","textObjs":[{"text":"That is exactly what I say and I would say that would not be the case had 10 years ago, had there been an adjudication that this type of pricing was illegal, then -- then we're unnoticed.","start":2822.545,"stop":2833.067,"duration":10.52},{"text":"We've known all this time that it's illegal, but here where they are attacking it for the first time.","start":2833.067,"stop":2841.161,"duration":8.09},{"text":"I think that it's only fair in the break and take handy cases and all the other types of cases where they knew how to do it.","start":2841.161,"stop":2847.898,"duration":6.74},{"text":"They have done it that way.","start":2847.898,"stop":2849.002,"duration":1.1},{"text":"They bring in all the people under complaints and one way or another, in the building around that goes into that type of a proceeding against an established practice in an industry, you end up with one specimen case going on up finally for the ultimate determination of the issue.","start":2849.002,"stop":2866.016,"duration":17.01},{"text":"It's been done.","start":2866.016,"stop":2866.846,"duration":0.83}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"You brought in one initial (Inaudible) I haven't thought of, but have there been any cases before that was given new reason for this particular time of discount?","start":2866.846,"stop":2881.09,"duration":14.24}]},{"speakerName":"Charles R. Sprowl","textObjs":[{"text":"None at all.","start":2881.09,"stop":2882.519,"duration":1.43},{"text":"The only language in it was -- that I was able to find was we know that -- that there are certain types of discounts, there have been questions such as in the Salt cases where there was a discount.","start":2882.519,"stop":2893.752,"duration":11.23},{"text":"It was available only to the one limited type of very large purchase.","start":2893.752,"stop":2899.694,"duration":5.94},{"text":"But as your -- this Court pointed out in Bruce's Juices.","start":2899.694,"stop":2902.575,"duration":2.88},{"text":"We aren't saying that so far from saying that all quantity discounts are just rendered illegal per se and it was the feeling of the industry that they were not illegal and when they were reasonable and available to every customer within reasonable interest and of course the Court of Appeals have held otherwise.","start":2902.575,"stop":2922.14,"duration":19.57}]},{"speakerName":"Tom C. Clark","textObjs":[{"text":"Of course (Inaudible) would not be illegal if the cost justification (Inaudible) --","start":2922.14,"stop":2930.236,"duration":8.1}]},{"speakerName":"Charles R. Sprowl","textObjs":[{"text":"That's right, but I'm not permitted to discuss that here.","start":2930.236,"stop":2934.333,"duration":4.1}]},{"speakerName":"Tom C. Clark","textObjs":[{"text":"That would mean that you have (Inaudible)","start":2934.333,"stop":2942.319,"duration":7.99}]},{"speakerName":"Charles R. Sprowl","textObjs":[{"text":"16.","start":2942.319,"stop":2942.711,"duration":0.39}]},{"speakerName":"Tom C. Clark","textObjs":[{"text":"-- operators at least 16 -- 16 men from 16 different countries to prove that there was no violation because of the falsity of the decision.","start":2942.711,"stop":2955.55,"duration":12.84}]},{"speakerName":"Charles R. Sprowl","textObjs":[{"text":"That's right, but it wouldn't take it on a terminable language and not a few proceeding against them all at once.","start":2955.55,"stop":2963.464,"duration":7.91},{"text":"I -- I think that had we done that here, we -- we would have no problem and even if they issued cease and desist order, that problem is always present even after a cease and desist order has been acted.","start":2963.464,"stop":2975.303,"duration":11.84},{"text":"You're then brought into a proceeding charged with violation.","start":2975.303,"stop":2978.711,"duration":3.41},{"text":"You are still entitled to show that no I'm not violating because although I did deviate the price, I did it either (a) because I met an equally low price with a competitor or (b) I can cost justify the discount.","start":2978.711,"stop":2990.077,"duration":11.37}]},{"speakerName":"Tom C. Clark","textObjs":[{"text":"Who said that it should (Inaudible)","start":2990.077,"stop":2992.996,"duration":2.92}]},{"speakerName":"Charles R. Sprowl","textObjs":[{"text":"That's true even after the orders are rendered.","start":2992.996,"stop":2995.814,"duration":2.82},{"text":"That's right.","start":2995.814,"stop":2995.906,"duration":0.09}]},{"speakerName":"Tom C. Clark","textObjs":[{"text":"Suppose your -- suppose your (Inaudible)","start":2995.906,"stop":3020.573,"duration":24.67}]},{"speakerName":"Charles R. Sprowl","textObjs":[{"text":"No, I don't think the Commission could curtail their right to make their defenses.","start":3020.573,"stop":3026.035,"duration":5.46},{"text":"My point is that they should have started this long ago when we first suggested that it isn't -- the fault doesn't lie in our door.","start":3026.035,"stop":3033.999,"duration":7.96},{"text":"We -- we are --","start":3033.999,"stop":3034.925,"duration":0.93}]},{"speakerName":"Tom C. Clark","textObjs":[{"text":"I understand that.","start":3034.925,"stop":3035.507,"duration":0.58}]},{"speakerName":"Charles R. Sprowl","textObjs":[{"text":"Now.","start":3035.507,"stop":3035.762,"duration":0.26}]},{"speakerName":"Tom C. Clark","textObjs":[{"text":"I understood you have submitted.","start":3035.762,"stop":3037.778,"duration":2.02}]},{"speakerName":"Charles R. Sprowl","textObjs":[{"text":"I say this that it -- it this is affirmed, that it's a simple enough matter for the Commission to show on -- on affidavit or motion to the Court of Appeals for the Seventh Circuit that we now have the cease and desist orders against this competitor and that competitor and the next competitor and -- and it certainly doesn't have to be against 18, because I can sit down with Mr. Kintner drawing the 10 principle, small competitors that were concerned with and that showing would be sufficient, I'm sure, to get the entry of the order.","start":3037.778,"stop":3068.055,"duration":30.28}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Sprowl, 16 or 17 as you see it, the Commission would issue a complaint against the 16 or 17, is that right?","start":3068.055,"stop":3078.412,"duration":10.36}]},{"speakerName":"Charles R. Sprowl","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes sir.","start":3078.412,"stop":3079.814,"duration":1.4},{"text":"That's right.","start":3079.814,"stop":3081.062,"duration":1.25}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Bring them in as you see it, making it (Inaudible), how long do you think it would take the Commission to get the kind of prima facie order, presumptive illegality against which there would be individualize defenses.","start":3081.062,"stop":3098.938,"duration":17.88},{"text":"You said they would -- it wouldn't take the Court -- it wouldn't ask the court to hold up enforcement against you until everyone of the 17 respondents or whatever they're called before the Commission, make their individual defenses, a generalize order which would take care of it.","start":3098.938,"stop":3117.675,"duration":18.74}]},{"speakerName":"Charles R. Sprowl","textObjs":[{"text":"No, because (Voice Overlap).","start":3117.675,"stop":3119.023,"duration":1.35},{"text":"Yes, there are some of those that are admittedly small.","start":3119.023,"stop":3122.014,"duration":2.99}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"How long from your point -- just on experience on these matters, how long do you think before the Commission could administratively sure an order that would take care of the unfairness that you are --","start":3122.014,"stop":3136.043,"duration":14.03}]},{"speakerName":"Charles R. Sprowl","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, it seemed to me, Your Honor that they would -- should be able to issue the complaint and carry it through their own evidence and the evidence of the respondent and get a commission order within 24 months, with the -- with the question of the general legality of the pricing system now settled by the decision.","start":3136.043,"stop":3155.72,"duration":19.68}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"And in that estimate, you include that the Commission has a lot of things to do.","start":3155.72,"stop":3159.504,"duration":3.78}]},{"speakerName":"Charles R. Sprowl","textObjs":[{"text":"That's right.","start":3159.504,"stop":3160.554,"duration":1.05}]},{"speakerName":"William O. Douglas","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible)","start":3160.554,"stop":3167.3,"duration":6.75}]},{"speakerName":"Charles R. Sprowl","textObjs":[{"text":"That is correct.","start":3167.3,"stop":3168.853,"duration":1.55},{"text":"Well, I won't -- I won't put it that way of -- that we are not as you have established to anybody's satisfaction.","start":3168.853,"stop":3177.895,"duration":9.04},{"text":"There are only two defenses they can make, either that they meet an equally low price.","start":3177.895,"stop":3182.268,"duration":4.37}]},{"speakerName":"William O. Douglas","textObjs":[{"text":"And yet you can't sue (Inaudible)","start":3182.268,"stop":3190.114,"duration":7.85}]},{"speakerName":"Charles R. Sprowl","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, I'm certain to this that they are using an illegal pricing method and I can't assume that everyone of their sales is illegal, but I -- I am sure that there -- they would susceptible of a cease and desist order.","start":3190.114,"stop":3201.461,"duration":11.35}]},{"speakerName":"Tom C. Clark","textObjs":[{"text":"Of course it would be different -- it could be different in this case, isn't it, with reference to the cost justification and with reference to meeting the (Inaudible) --","start":3201.461,"stop":3215.611,"duration":14.15}]},{"speakerName":"Charles R. Sprowl","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, if the decisions in our case are correct.","start":3215.611,"stop":3218.642,"duration":3.03},{"text":"There is very little they can do in the way of cost justification.","start":3218.642,"stop":3222.663,"duration":4.02}]},{"speakerName":"Tom C. Clark","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible)","start":3222.663,"stop":3229.438,"duration":6.78}]},{"speakerName":"Charles R. Sprowl","textObjs":[{"text":"That's right, but we're -- we're about the smallest in the group.","start":3229.438,"stop":3232.622,"duration":3.18}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"You are the smallest?","start":3232.622,"stop":3233.707,"duration":1.09}]},{"speakerName":"Charles R. Sprowl","textObjs":[{"text":"One of the smallest in the group.","start":3233.707,"stop":3234.916,"duration":1.21},{"text":"$2 million is our annual gross sale.","start":3234.916,"stop":3237.507,"duration":2.59}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Who's smaller than that?","start":3237.507,"stop":3239.75,"duration":2.24},{"text":"One company is smaller than that?","start":3239.75,"stop":3240.851,"duration":1.1}]},{"speakerName":"Charles R. Sprowl","textObjs":[{"text":"I say that there -- no, there are some that are larger and some that are about the same size.","start":3240.851,"stop":3245.232,"duration":4.38},{"text":"There aren't any money that can be much smaller because you can't manufacture and sell in this business with much less volume than that.","start":3245.232,"stop":3254.895,"duration":9.66}]},{"speakerName":"Tom C. Clark","textObjs":[{"text":"Can I ask you just one other question?","start":3254.895,"stop":3256.372,"duration":1.48}]},{"speakerName":"Charles R. Sprowl","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes.","start":3256.372,"stop":3256.974,"duration":0.6}]},{"speakerName":"Tom C. Clark","textObjs":[{"text":"You said that (Inaudible)","start":3256.974,"stop":3274.876,"duration":17.9}]},{"speakerName":"Charles R. Sprowl","textObjs":[{"text":"Oh, no.","start":3274.876,"stop":3275.175,"duration":0.3},{"text":"I think they first have to permit all the evidence to be adduced in the way of defense.","start":3275.175,"stop":3280.454,"duration":5.28},{"text":"They have to make their proof, but my point is they have decided that this type of pricing method is illegal now.","start":3280.454,"stop":3287.56,"duration":7.11}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"What individualize the term that's then left under the cease and desist order?","start":3287.56,"stop":3292.275,"duration":4.72}]},{"speakerName":"Charles R. Sprowl","textObjs":[{"text":"Once you have a cease -- whether before after the cease and desist order is entered as Your Honors stated in the Ruberoid case, the statutory defense is that they're always inherently available, even though if you're charged of violating that order.","start":3292.275,"stop":3305.892,"duration":13.62},{"text":"You can still show that the reason you reduced your price was to meet the equally low price the competitors would pay or you can show that you did it on a cost justification basis and that is inherently read into every cease and desist order.","start":3305.892,"stop":3318.828,"duration":12.94}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Did you do that now?","start":3318.828,"stop":3320.323,"duration":1.49}]},{"speakerName":"Charles R. Sprowl","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes.","start":3320.323,"stop":3320.515,"duration":0.19}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, suppose this order would not (Inaudible) these people are using discounts?","start":3320.515,"stop":3333.828,"duration":13.31}]},{"speakerName":"Charles R. Sprowl","textObjs":[{"text":"Not on the very same thing.","start":3333.828,"stop":3335.207,"duration":1.38},{"text":"Let's say we went to a uniform price after the order is affirmed which we would have to do, but that to keep one customer, we cut our price 10% in the Dallas area.","start":3335.207,"stop":3345.036,"duration":9.83},{"text":"That would be in my mind defensible even though we were under a cease and desist order.We did it in good faith to keep a customer we already have.","start":3345.036,"stop":3351.575,"duration":6.54}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"It couldn't defend the system but you defend the individual case?","start":3351.575,"stop":3355.089,"duration":3.51}]},{"speakerName":"Charles R. Sprowl","textObjs":[{"text":"That's right, after the entry of the order.","start":3355.089,"stop":3359.285,"duration":4.2}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Sprowl, your time has expired, but we thank you so much for your time in question for the -- if in rebuttal we would like to ask a few more minutes --","start":3359.285,"stop":3368.074,"duration":8.79}]},{"speakerName":"Charles R. Sprowl","textObjs":[{"text":"Thank you.","start":3368.074,"stop":3368.509,"duration":0.43}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"-- to summarize your argument (Inaudible)","start":3368.509,"stop":3371.608,"duration":3.1}]},{"speakerName":"Charles R. Sprowl","textObjs":[{"text":"Thank you, Mr. Chief Justice.","start":3371.608,"stop":3373.667,"duration":2.06}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Kintner.","start":3373.667,"stop":3375.215,"duration":1.55}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"-- please the Court.","start":3375.215,"stop":3377.178,"duration":1.96},{"text":"Mr. Sprowl has mentioned the smallness of his concern.","start":3377.178,"stop":3381.639,"duration":4.46},{"text":"In the eyes of the Commission, it is a principal factor in the industry.","start":3381.639,"stop":3385.567,"duration":3.93},{"text":"The two principal competitors of this concerned are Sorensen and P.& D., both of whom have outstanding cease and desist orders entered against them affirmed by Courts of Appeal.","start":3385.567,"stop":3399.035,"duration":13.47},{"text":"The respondent herein has a volume -- annual volume of about $2 million, Sorensen and P.& D., $1,685,000 and $1,300,000 respectively.","start":3399.035,"stop":3414.975,"duration":15.94}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"When -- when did you obtain those orders?","start":3414.975,"stop":3420.024,"duration":5.05}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"Within the past few months, there have been six orders, three of them -- four have been either or have been before this Court.","start":3420.024,"stop":3432.318,"duration":12.29},{"text":"The two cases -- two instant cases, the Edelmann case which is here on writ of certiorari, request for a writ of certiorari, the Whittaker case where the -- this Court denied writ of certiorari and the Sorensen and P.& D. cases affirmed by the courts below.","start":3432.318,"stop":3452.135,"duration":19.82}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Now, are they all names of -- they're quoted in the 16 or 18 to make a --","start":3452.135,"stop":3457.266,"duration":5.13}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"No, sir, two of them.","start":3457.266,"stop":3458.282,"duration":1.02},{"text":"Sorensen and P.& D. are included upon --","start":3458.282,"stop":3462.008,"duration":3.73}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"In this industry.","start":3462.008,"stop":3463.486,"duration":1.48}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"-- of the Niehoff competitors.","start":3463.486,"stop":3466.256,"duration":2.77},{"text":"That's the difficulty and Niehoff refers to 16 or 18 competitors, but it's the same situation I mentioned.","start":3466.256,"stop":3473.586,"duration":7.33},{"text":"A and B compete with C.","start":3473.586,"stop":3475.963,"duration":2.38},{"text":"C competes with A and B, but also competes with D and E, those that you have a never ending situation.","start":3475.963,"stop":3484.031,"duration":8.07},{"text":"Each competitor and each person in the industry has -- has different competitors.","start":3484.031,"stop":3490.437,"duration":6.41},{"text":"They -- it is not a -- an industry and a margin of this industry where each competes with the other, but it is an industry of 75 lines where some factors such as Niehoff here handle only three lines and are preempted in one ignition as our P.& D. and Sorensen.","start":3490.437,"stop":3514.19,"duration":23.75}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"But you hold against (Inaudible)","start":3514.19,"stop":3518.558,"duration":4.37}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"No, sir.","start":3518.558,"stop":3520.674,"duration":2.12},{"text":"We expect to move to secure compliance against them as well as others, against whom the Commission has --","start":3520.674,"stop":3530.463,"duration":9.79}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, didn't you say that the orders against them had been sustained in the Courts of Appeal?","start":3530.463,"stop":3535.832,"duration":5.37}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"That is correct, the Sorensen case sustained by the District of Columbia Court of Appeals and the P.& D. sustained by the Seventh Circuit.","start":3535.832,"stop":3547.24,"duration":11.41}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, why -- why do they have to move the compliance?","start":3547.24,"stop":3549.365,"duration":2.13},{"text":"Are they still in disobedience?","start":3549.365,"stop":3552.38,"duration":3.02}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"They have the 60-day period in which they may comply with the order and then they may ask us on a staff level for an additional 60 days and then we start negotiations, serious negotiations to bring -- adjust their business practices and that as I pointed out earlier is a long arduous process.","start":3552.38,"stop":3573.608,"duration":21.23}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible)","start":3573.608,"stop":3576.597,"duration":2.99}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"Before we go back to the courts for assistance.","start":3576.597,"stop":3580.66,"duration":4.06}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"I just thought to ask you a question (Inaudible)","start":3580.66,"stop":3608.796,"duration":28.14}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"It would certainly be a matter which you should bring to the Commission's attention.","start":3608.796,"stop":3613.971,"duration":5.18},{"text":"The -- the -- at the compliance stage.","start":3613.971,"stop":3617.062,"duration":3.09}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible) to meet that equally low price brought on by that discount --","start":3617.062,"stop":3621.122,"duration":4.06}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, that would be a -- it could be a defense under certain circumstances in the original proceeding, the meeting of an equally low price of a competitor.","start":3621.122,"stop":3632.873,"duration":11.75},{"text":"Actually, there are various defenses other than the two mentioned.","start":3632.873,"stop":3637.919,"duration":5.05}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"But I'm --","start":3637.919,"stop":3638.049,"duration":0.13}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"It --","start":3638.049,"stop":3638.305,"duration":0.26}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"-- talking about now after the order was entered.","start":3638.305,"stop":3640.241,"duration":1.94},{"text":"You decide -- you accused them of violating and that he gave that discount to somebody (Inaudible).","start":3640.241,"stop":3647.941,"duration":7.7},{"text":"The company then said, “Yes, we gave that discount with our competitor.”","start":3647.941,"stop":3652.409,"duration":4.47},{"text":"(Inaudible)","start":3652.409,"stop":3655.533,"duration":3.12}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"He -- he can raise that defense of meeting competition at the second and the third stages of the proceeding.","start":3655.533,"stop":3663.357,"duration":7.82},{"text":"He can raise it when the Commission proves the second violation and goes to a Court of Appeals for a decree of enforcement and then he can bite his time and after the Commission has proved to its satisfaction a third violation and goes to the Court of Appeals and ask for contempt.","start":3663.357,"stop":3679.558,"duration":16.2},{"text":"He can still tell the Court, “Well after all, all I was doing was meeting competition.”","start":3679.558,"stop":3684.046,"duration":4.49}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Meaning he can do that on this particular order into his name?","start":3684.046,"stop":3687.092,"duration":3.05}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"He can do it at anyone of the three stages, if Your Honor please.","start":3687.092,"stop":3690.738,"duration":3.65}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Do I understand --","start":3690.738,"stop":3691.664,"duration":0.93}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"That's what makes that law so difficult to enforce.","start":3691.664,"stop":3694.617,"duration":2.95},{"text":"We're doing the best we can.","start":3694.617,"stop":3696.473,"duration":1.86}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Do I understand that Mr. Sprowl (Inaudible).","start":3696.473,"stop":3705.36,"duration":8.89},{"text":"He then say, “Oh, I've done nothing illegal because I was merely (Inaudible) my illegality between another illegality.","start":3705.36,"stop":3713.304,"duration":7.94},{"text":"Is that what you're talking about?","start":3713.304,"stop":3716.43,"duration":3.13}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"As I understand it, Mr. Sprowl was referring to the so-called 2 (b) defense under the Robinson-Patman Act, which is really another lawsuit and a very difficult subject as -- subject matter as Your Honor appreciates.","start":3716.43,"stop":3736.795,"duration":20.37},{"text":"But there is such a defense and as I understand it, Mr. Sprowl says that under certain circumstances, he -- he would use that defense and could use it and the fact is that in this instance, the -- his -- his client did vigorously contend to use a defense and it (Voice Overlap) --","start":3736.795,"stop":3755.978,"duration":19.18}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"But he -- but he lost that defense.","start":3755.978,"stop":3757.54,"duration":1.56}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"He certainly did, sir, and lost on the other defense that he used.","start":3757.54,"stop":3760.146,"duration":2.61}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"And it -- is his lost going to be a victory if you were to order the illegality against the competitors?","start":3760.146,"stop":3767.079,"duration":6.93}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"The same time that he was making this defense --","start":3767.079,"stop":3768.843,"duration":1.76}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"That was sophisticated for an argument.","start":3768.843,"stop":3770.546,"duration":1.7}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"He was piously saying, “Well, we -- we think you're wrong here.","start":3770.546,"stop":3776.234,"duration":5.69},{"text":"We -- we -- we're going to defend ourselves.","start":3776.234,"stop":3778.537,"duration":2.3},{"text":"We're vigorously defending ourselves, but at the same time we want you to bear in mind that there are certain of our competitors you haven't proceeded against.","start":3778.537,"stop":3786.23,"duration":7.69},{"text":"You've got to get them too, regardless of whether our defense wins or loses in this case.”","start":3786.23,"stop":3792.08,"duration":5.85}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Have you exposed that (Inaudible) in your brief?","start":3792.08,"stop":3795.42,"duration":3.34}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"I hope so, but if I haven't, Judge Finnegan has in his dissent in the lower court.","start":3795.42,"stop":3802.426,"duration":7.01},{"text":"He says that it appears that the majority's modification compels the Commission to investigate or complete examination of Niehoff competitors at the risk of (Inaudible) and otherwise approved order, whether this entails all 19 competitors or a baker's dozen is unrevealed.","start":3802.426,"stop":3821.169,"duration":18.74},{"text":"My grave doubts that our statutory power to modify Federal Trade Commission orders can be converted into policing and supervision -- supervising, though perhaps obliquely, the length and breadth and sequence of Commission investigations brings me to the position I now take.","start":3821.169,"stop":3838.415,"duration":17.25},{"text":"Certainly, we would refuse to activate the Commission upon a bare petition for mandamus to investigate the automotive ignition industry, responsibility of achieving enforcement of the statutes Congress assigned to the Commission lies elsewhere.","start":3838.415,"stop":3854.273,"duration":15.86}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"That's a very different thing from saying that if you bring the law under the heel of the law, they'd all scot-free.","start":3854.273,"stop":3863.674,"duration":9.4}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"The practical effect if the Commission were forced to this -- to these depths would be that all would go scot-free because in effect, the Commission would never complete an administrative procedure.","start":3863.674,"stop":3876.81,"duration":13.14}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"It's not because what was the illegal shall become legal by modification.","start":3876.81,"stop":3882.541,"duration":5.73}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"No, sir.","start":3882.541,"stop":3885.185,"duration":2.64}]},{"speakerName":"Tom C. Clark","textObjs":[{"text":"Suppose that you're condemned to say that they (Inaudible)","start":3885.185,"stop":3905.146,"duration":19.96},{"text":"Niehoff have a right to raise that (Inaudible)?","start":3905.146,"stop":3908.15,"duration":3}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"Oh, yes, sir.","start":3908.15,"stop":3909.684,"duration":1.53},{"text":"This would be another set of facts.","start":3909.684,"stop":3913.267,"duration":3.58}]},{"speakerName":"Tom C. Clark","textObjs":[{"text":"Why wouldn't it be protected here if its competitors continued to allow the discount if it was in cease and desist (Inaudible)","start":3913.267,"stop":3931.412,"duration":18.14}]},{"speakerName":"Earl W. Kintner","textObjs":[{"text":"If I were advising his client.","start":3931.412,"stop":3933.031,"duration":1.62},{"text":"I advised his client to look into that situation meeting competition.","start":3933.031,"stop":3938.973,"duration":5.94},{"text":"I don't think they're obliged to sell at one price.","start":3938.973,"stop":3944.484,"duration":5.51},{"text":"I don't think they're obliged to sell at their maximum price.","start":3944.484,"stop":3949.03,"duration":4.55},{"text":"I don't know what price they'll have to adopt or what prices to comply with the order here, but it is incumbent on them to reexamine their business practices just as it is this entire industry to reexamine its business practices.","start":3949.03,"stop":3966.539,"duration":17.51},{"text":"Counsel says he hasn't had any notice.","start":3966.539,"stop":3968.975,"duration":2.44},{"text":"He should have read the Morton Salt case.","start":3968.975,"stop":3971.907,"duration":2.93},{"text":"He should have read the various decision of the Commission which cast grave doubt on the validity of these cumulative annual discount arrangements.","start":3971.907,"stop":3983.477,"duration":11.57},{"text":"Typically, they have had no basis or relationship to cost.","start":3983.477,"stop":3988.366,"duration":4.89},{"text":"It is not to say that per se illegal, but typically, I say they have had no -- they -- there were no relationship to cost and it was incumbent upon any counsel conversion with the law to examine such accumulative annual discount rebate system of pricing.","start":3988.366,"stop":4007.321,"duration":18.95},{"text":"Thank you, Your Honors.","start":4007.321,"stop":4009.553,"duration":2.23}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Sprowl.","start":4009.553,"stop":4012.328,"duration":2.78}]},{"speakerName":"Charles R. Sprowl","textObjs":[{"text":"I only like to say one thing, Mr. Chief Justice.","start":4012.328,"stop":4017.294,"duration":4.97},{"text":"I think that perhaps I have misled the Court on the 2 (b) defense.","start":4017.294,"stop":4022.962,"duration":5.67},{"text":"The type of 2 (b) defense that Niehoff was endeavoring to make in this case was that you aren't required to meet a competitor's price locally at the point of sale to keep a customer, but it's -- you come within the defense if you meet a nationwide pattern of price discounts established by your competition and that, the Court has held in this case that, “No, that is not a 2 (b) defense.”","start":4022.962,"stop":4050.873,"duration":27.91},{"text":"It isn't sufficient to show that in good faith, you granted these discounts which aren't quite identical to any competitor discount but are substantially about the same of every competitor's discount and you've done it nationwide as a consistent method of meeting their discount in competition that you are not really establishing a cost justification defense.","start":4050.873,"stop":4073.477,"duration":22.6},{"text":"So, as far as this case is concerned, our cost justification then did accept for a very isolated situation where we might have lowered the price to keep an established customer which I'm sure the Commission would let us report and would never make a court case out of it because it's so isolated in local situation.","start":4073.477,"stop":4093.98,"duration":20.5}]},{"speakerName":"Tom C. Clark","textObjs":[{"text":"What about meeting the price of the competitors.","start":4093.98,"stop":4098.666,"duration":4.69}]},{"speakerName":"Charles R. Sprowl","textObjs":[{"text":"That is -- that is the point I am making.","start":4098.666,"stop":4100.701,"duration":2.03},{"text":"In other words, if I have --if Niehoff should have a customer in Detroit at which it is selling at its least price, then a standard manufacturing company which is one of Niehoff's principal competitor shows up and says, “Look, I can sell you this same product and it is the same at 10% lower.”","start":4100.701,"stop":4123.301,"duration":22.6},{"text":"Then, Niehoff is entitled to lower its price to keep that customer, but that's very -- that's a local situation.","start":4123.301,"stop":4131.631,"duration":8.33},{"text":"I'm sure, even after a cease and desist order is entered, that's the type of thing you would report to the Commission and I -- there is no question.","start":4131.631,"stop":4138.921,"duration":7.29}]},{"speakerName":"Tom C. Clark","textObjs":[{"text":"I understand that, but assuming you did not get to say that (Inaudible)","start":4138.921,"stop":4159.148,"duration":20.23}]},{"speakerName":"Charles R. Sprowl","textObjs":[{"text":"It would be very difficult.","start":4159.148,"stop":4161.131,"duration":1.98}]},{"speakerName":"Tom C. Clark","textObjs":[{"text":"In a legal standpoint?","start":4161.131,"stop":4163.274,"duration":2.14}]},{"speakerName":"Charles R. Sprowl","textObjs":[{"text":"Perhaps, from a legal standpoint, sir.","start":4163.274,"stop":4164.596,"duration":1.32}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Although a cease and desist order is right against --","start":4164.596,"stop":4167.988,"duration":3.39}]},{"speakerName":"Charles R. Sprowl","textObjs":[{"text":"I don't think -- after the cease and desist order is out, I think that perhaps if we were -- if we knew of it and we knew it was a bona fide attempt on standards to cut the price and -- and we were satisfied to that then even though we've gone to a single price, I think 2 (b) would permit you to put the practicalities and you never know it until they both say it.","start":4167.988,"stop":4188.403,"duration":20.41}]},{"speakerName":"Tom C. Clark","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible)","start":4188.403,"stop":4189.921,"duration":1.52}]},{"speakerName":"Charles R. Sprowl","textObjs":[{"text":"That's right.","start":4189.921,"stop":4190.499,"duration":0.58},{"text":"They've -- they have taken the customer and then we know about it and we can't get them back.","start":4190.499,"stop":4196.159,"duration":5.66},{"text":"Thank you.","start":4196.159,"stop":4208.453,"duration":12.29}]}]}],"decidedBy":"Warren Court","arguedOn":"Jan 14, 1958","petitioner":"Moog Industries, Inc.","respondent":"Federal Trade Commission","docket":"77","citation":"355 US 411 (1958)","justiaLink":"https://supreme.justia.com/cases/federal/us/355/411","lowerCourt":"United States Court of Appeals for the Eighth Circuit","grantedOn":"","decidedOn":"Jan 27, 1958"}